00:01:32.420 --> 00:01:34.970
Sari Nusseibeh is professor
of Islamic and Political

00:01:34.970 --> 00:01:39.800
Philosophy at Al-Quds University
East Jerusalem, where he served

00:01:39.800 --> 00:01:44.390
as president from 1995 to 2014.

00:01:44.390 --> 00:01:47.270
He taught at Birzeit
University in the West Bank

00:01:47.270 --> 00:01:50.750
from '78 to '91,
when he was placed

00:01:50.750 --> 00:01:55.430
on administrative detention
in an Israeli jail for three

00:01:55.430 --> 00:01:56.990
months.

00:01:56.990 --> 00:02:01.520
He has founded and chaired
several grass roots committees,

00:02:01.520 --> 00:02:06.740
unions, and NGOs, including,
in 2002, the People's Voice,

00:02:06.740 --> 00:02:09.770
a [? bi-national ?] public
campaign for a two state

00:02:09.770 --> 00:02:11.450
solution.

00:02:11.450 --> 00:02:14.390
His latest books include
Once Upon A Country,

00:02:14.390 --> 00:02:19.280
A Palestinian Life, What Is
A Palestinian State Worth,

00:02:19.280 --> 00:02:23.660
The Story of Reason in
Islam, and most recently,

00:02:23.660 --> 00:02:28.640
[INAUDIBLE] Al [? shifa. ?]
He was the Rita Hauser

00:02:28.640 --> 00:02:32.300
fellow at Radcliffe
in 2004 and 2005

