00:03:11.320 --> 00:03:15.410
To the study of political
philosophy and social ethics,

00:03:15.410 --> 00:03:18.990
Sari brings remarkable
blend of scholarly insight

00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:22.680
and pragmatic
strategic intelligence.

00:03:22.680 --> 00:03:24.900
The depth of his learning
in medieval and modern

00:03:24.900 --> 00:03:27.270
Islamic philosophy
is only matched

00:03:27.270 --> 00:03:30.540
by the range of his
expertise in traditions

00:03:30.540 --> 00:03:34.380
of Western liberal thought
and ethical theory.

00:03:34.380 --> 00:03:37.200
Sari's personal and
professional involvement

00:03:37.200 --> 00:03:40.290
with many significant
Israeli-Palestinian peace

00:03:40.290 --> 00:03:44.880
initiatives gives his
view a rare authority.

00:03:44.880 --> 00:03:47.100
While fully aware
of the importance

00:03:47.100 --> 00:03:50.130
of pragmatic and
strategic maneuvers,

00:03:50.130 --> 00:03:53.790
Sari conceives of the
process of negotiation

00:03:53.790 --> 00:03:57.780
as an ethical practice that
must be fully committed

00:03:57.780 --> 00:04:02.280
to the mutuality and
dignity of the antagonist.

00:04:02.280 --> 00:04:06.990
And it is from Sari that I have
learned very important issues

00:04:06.990 --> 00:04:13.440
about the ethics of negotiation
sometimes deployed in meetings.

00:04:13.440 --> 00:04:18.390
At other times, just
conceptually speculative,

00:04:18.390 --> 00:04:19.140
the idea--

00:04:19.140 --> 00:04:21.779
I remember once
in a conversation,

00:04:21.779 --> 00:04:25.720
that once you get into
the chamber to negotiate,

00:04:25.720 --> 00:04:28.870
you have a chance of
making your opponent.

00:04:28.870 --> 00:04:32.010
Your opponent only doesn't
come to you as given.

00:04:32.010 --> 00:04:35.460
And then the other concept
that I remember is the--

00:04:35.460 --> 00:04:37.530
I won't get the words for it--

00:04:37.530 --> 00:04:42.330
is that one of the most
interesting ways of actually

00:04:42.330 --> 00:04:46.380
riding past the obstacles
that people bring with them

00:04:46.380 --> 00:04:50.370
is to put a kind
of idea or a goal

00:04:50.370 --> 00:04:53.610
outside of the
immediate negotiation

00:04:53.610 --> 00:04:57.670
so people always have a
horizon to work towards.

00:04:57.670 --> 00:05:02.070
And that gives a different sense
of scale to where you're going,

00:05:02.070 --> 00:05:04.440
and what you're speaking,
and what gains you want.

00:05:04.440 --> 00:05:11.310
So I like this idea, which
is both partly a distraction

00:05:11.310 --> 00:05:13.210
and a horizon--

00:05:13.210 --> 00:05:16.060
interesting strategy.

00:05:16.060 --> 00:05:18.700
Negotiation for Sari
is a noble calling.

00:05:18.700 --> 00:05:22.120
He insists on the
necessity, however remote

00:05:22.120 --> 00:05:26.410
or aspirational it may appear,
of open dialogue, in which

00:05:26.410 --> 00:05:28.390
the commitment to
the Palestinian cause

00:05:28.390 --> 00:05:32.380
does not prevent him from
seeing how aims, goals, and even

00:05:32.380 --> 00:05:38.020
values come to be transformed
in the processes of negotiation.

00:05:38.020 --> 00:05:40.780
Even in the darkest
times, Sari surpasses

00:05:40.780 --> 00:05:44.770
dogmas and orthodoxies
to suggest that in order

00:05:44.770 --> 00:05:47.590
to reach a workable
agreement, there

00:05:47.590 --> 00:05:50.620
has to be an ethical
commitment to the very process

00:05:50.620 --> 00:05:52.600
of negotiation.

