00:08:25.590 --> 00:08:30.480
Maybe I just want to start
off by saying that today there

00:08:30.480 --> 00:08:34.620
were municipal elections
and local elections

00:08:34.620 --> 00:08:37.380
in Jerusalem and
in Israel, in fact.

00:08:37.380 --> 00:08:40.770
And just like every other
year for the past 50 years,

00:08:40.770 --> 00:08:45.360
I think, ever since
1967, only a tiny portion

00:08:45.360 --> 00:08:48.150
of the Palestinians
in fact participated

00:08:48.150 --> 00:08:48.990
in those elections.

00:08:48.990 --> 00:08:51.840
I think less than 1%.

00:08:51.840 --> 00:08:55.800
Although this year,
there was an attempt

00:08:55.800 --> 00:08:58.680
by a group of Palestinians
from Jerusalem

00:08:58.680 --> 00:09:00.750
to participate in
those elections.

00:09:00.750 --> 00:09:01.980
But we can discuss this.

00:09:01.980 --> 00:09:06.000
Why is it that the
Palestinians in East Jerusalem

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:09.300
have, for all this
time, been opposed

00:09:09.300 --> 00:09:11.670
to participating in elections?

00:09:11.670 --> 00:09:16.620
And what does this mean
in the context of thinking

00:09:16.620 --> 00:09:18.450
about sharing the city?

00:09:18.450 --> 00:09:22.590
As you know, there are
perhaps between three and 400,

00:09:22.590 --> 00:09:26.850
or perhaps a bit over,
Palestinians in Jerusalem.

00:09:26.850 --> 00:09:33.330
And you know, they have
actually been living,

00:09:33.330 --> 00:09:40.830
since 1967, in a very strange
kind of suspended situation

00:09:40.830 --> 00:09:43.230
because they are not regarded--

00:09:43.230 --> 00:09:47.070
East Jerusalem is not regarded
by Israel as occupied,

00:09:47.070 --> 00:09:50.920
as the other territories.

00:09:50.920 --> 00:09:52.060
And it's annexed.

00:09:52.060 --> 00:09:55.090
So it falls under Israeli law.

00:09:55.090 --> 00:09:59.770
And the Palestinians, therefore,
are residents in Israel,

00:09:59.770 --> 00:10:03.550
insofar as they
are Jerusalemites.

00:10:03.550 --> 00:10:06.880
But they have not, in the
past 50 years, been involved.

00:10:06.880 --> 00:10:09.880
They haven't themselves
accepted to become

00:10:09.880 --> 00:10:11.920
involved in any of the--

00:10:11.920 --> 00:10:16.300
as a community-- in
the municipal elections

00:10:16.300 --> 00:10:19.960
or in any other
sort of institution

00:10:19.960 --> 00:10:22.630
in the Israeli system.

00:10:22.630 --> 00:10:25.540
Nonetheless, of
course, there have

00:10:25.540 --> 00:10:28.870
been also seeking
to find, together

00:10:28.870 --> 00:10:34.510
with Palestinian colleagues,
people in the rest of the West

00:10:34.510 --> 00:10:37.990
Bank in Gaza, trying to find
a national solution, not

00:10:37.990 --> 00:10:41.080
a municipal solution,
to their problem

00:10:41.080 --> 00:10:43.180
in the context of a
two state solution.

00:10:43.180 --> 00:10:47.410
And they've been involved
in the negotiations,

00:10:47.410 --> 00:10:52.630
along with other Palestinians,
in the context of that attempt

00:10:52.630 --> 00:10:54.130
to reach a two state solution.

00:10:54.130 --> 00:10:58.060
And unfortunately, as
you probably all know,

00:10:58.060 --> 00:11:03.680
that process has not really
borne any fruit so far.

00:11:03.680 --> 00:11:07.420
And if anything, in
fact, it looks like--

00:11:07.420 --> 00:11:10.850
looked at objectively,
rationally speaking--

00:11:10.850 --> 00:11:14.950
it looks like it's
been a failure.

00:11:14.950 --> 00:11:19.810
And that day after
day, year after year,

00:11:19.810 --> 00:11:23.290
we're being pushed, I
think, both sides, maybe,

00:11:23.290 --> 00:11:28.340
by default, into
a single system.

00:11:28.340 --> 00:11:34.330
But not a system in which
the two parties are partners,

00:11:34.330 --> 00:11:39.280
but it is a system in which
one party is basically sitting

00:11:39.280 --> 00:11:41.540
on top of the other party.

00:11:41.540 --> 00:11:44.480
And in Jerusalem in
particular, there

00:11:44.480 --> 00:11:49.150
have been problems
that in a sense

00:11:49.150 --> 00:11:53.530
exemplify this
very odd situation.

00:11:53.530 --> 00:11:59.260
The problems have been
the slow, if you like,

00:11:59.260 --> 00:12:05.950
displacement of Palestinians
in the city-- displacement not

00:12:05.950 --> 00:12:12.370
only as individuals, but also
as a culture, as street names,

00:12:12.370 --> 00:12:14.050
as properties.

00:12:14.050 --> 00:12:18.250
In the past few weeks, there
have been various attempts,

00:12:18.250 --> 00:12:23.050
successful attempts, to take
over some Arab properties

00:12:23.050 --> 00:12:27.550
in the old city, buying Arab
properties in the Old City.

00:12:27.550 --> 00:12:30.310
And this has created
a lot of noise

00:12:30.310 --> 00:12:32.720
among Jerusalemites,
among Arab Jerusalemites,

00:12:32.720 --> 00:12:41.440
as a way of expressing anxiety
about their status in the city.

00:12:41.440 --> 00:12:45.760
In other words, we are living in
a situation that doesn't really

00:12:45.760 --> 00:12:50.200
give us much [? chance ?]
on the Palestinian side

00:12:50.200 --> 00:12:53.980
to think in terms
of an equitable

00:12:53.980 --> 00:12:56.320
engagement with the other side.

00:12:56.320 --> 00:13:02.717
Now this morning, I was
asking my son, my eldest son--

00:13:02.717 --> 00:13:04.092
you know, I was
telling him I was

00:13:04.092 --> 00:13:08.270
going to talk about sharing, and
what should I say about that.

00:13:08.270 --> 00:13:11.200
And he said, well,
there are three ways

00:13:11.200 --> 00:13:12.560
of looking at sharing.

00:13:12.560 --> 00:13:15.520
One is you divide things up.

00:13:15.520 --> 00:13:17.390
You have an orange.

00:13:17.390 --> 00:13:19.100
And you divide it
up in the middle,

00:13:19.100 --> 00:13:22.450
and you sort of give
one part to the one side

00:13:22.450 --> 00:13:24.140
and the other to the other.

00:13:24.140 --> 00:13:28.180
And the other way of
doing it is to peel it.

00:13:28.180 --> 00:13:32.270
And then maybe the other party
will take either the orange

00:13:32.270 --> 00:13:34.720
or the peel.

00:13:34.720 --> 00:13:37.510
[LAUGHTER] And that
has to do with--

00:13:37.510 --> 00:13:40.450
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

00:13:40.450 --> 00:13:45.290
--that has to do with what your
needs are, or concerns are.

00:13:45.290 --> 00:13:48.650
So you know, one party
may just need the peel.

00:13:48.650 --> 00:13:50.220
So you give it to them.

00:13:50.220 --> 00:13:52.760
And the other party
needs the actual orange.

00:13:52.760 --> 00:13:58.880
But the third way, he said,
was to think of it, or sharing,

00:13:58.880 --> 00:14:00.410
as an idea.

00:14:00.410 --> 00:14:02.520
And I told him what
does that mean?

00:14:02.520 --> 00:14:04.840
And he said, well,
in sharing an idea,

00:14:04.840 --> 00:14:08.990
there is no giving things
away to somebody else.

00:14:08.990 --> 00:14:11.720
You maintain possession,
if you like--

00:14:11.720 --> 00:14:16.490
you and the other of the thing
that you have before you.

00:14:16.490 --> 00:14:20.600
And he said to me, well,
Jerusalem can be like that.

00:14:20.600 --> 00:14:22.050
Jerusalem can be an idea.

00:14:22.050 --> 00:14:25.940
And I thought about this on the
train today to see whether I

00:14:25.940 --> 00:14:31.160
can agree with him
and decided I can't.

00:14:31.160 --> 00:14:34.190
Because I thought, well,
even as an idea, people,

00:14:34.190 --> 00:14:38.720
different parties actually can
disagree over what the idea is.

00:14:38.720 --> 00:14:42.200
And we end up, in
fact, needing to

00:14:42.200 --> 00:14:47.030
once again having to come
to terms with one another.

00:14:47.030 --> 00:14:51.020
Let me go back to the beginning
and then to talk a little bit

00:14:51.020 --> 00:14:53.090
about the word sharing.

00:14:53.090 --> 00:14:56.480
When I first started talking
or thinking about sharing,

00:14:56.480 --> 00:15:01.860
it was on the basis of listening
to my sons and daughter--

00:15:01.860 --> 00:15:04.040
no, sons-- my daughter, not yet.

00:15:04.040 --> 00:15:07.220
But my sons telling
their kids, when

00:15:07.220 --> 00:15:10.220
they started fighting
with one another

00:15:10.220 --> 00:15:13.970
over a piece of chocolate
or a cake or something,

00:15:13.970 --> 00:15:18.200
and I'll hear them
tell their kids

00:15:18.200 --> 00:15:22.310
you should share with your
brother or your sister.

00:15:22.310 --> 00:15:25.820
And I started thinking
about that, what that means.

00:15:25.820 --> 00:15:32.240
And decided, really, what that
means at the end of the day is

00:15:32.240 --> 00:15:35.690
that you should be able to
somehow respect the other--

00:15:35.690 --> 00:15:38.960
your brother, in this
case, or sister--

00:15:38.960 --> 00:15:41.870
as an equal individual being.

00:15:41.870 --> 00:15:46.160
And when I started trying to
think about how to apply this

00:15:46.160 --> 00:15:49.500
to Jerusalem, I
started thinking, well,

00:15:49.500 --> 00:15:52.550
you can't really do any
sharing between Israelis

00:15:52.550 --> 00:15:55.850
and Palestinians until
and unless we somehow

00:15:55.850 --> 00:15:59.760
come to see each other
as equal human beings.

00:15:59.760 --> 00:16:05.160
Now at some points in
the past 50 years--

00:16:05.160 --> 00:16:07.490
[INAUDIBLE] just
mentioned, for instance,

00:16:07.490 --> 00:16:11.690
my longstanding relationship
with [? Avishai ?] and many

00:16:11.690 --> 00:16:13.730
other examples--

00:16:13.730 --> 00:16:17.390
at some points, I could
see that, in fact, Israelis

00:16:17.390 --> 00:16:21.530
and Palestinians could, in fact,
look upon each other as equals

00:16:21.530 --> 00:16:24.350
and respect each other
and, therefore, would

00:16:24.350 --> 00:16:29.120
be prepared to share with
the other whatever needs

00:16:29.120 --> 00:16:30.860
to be shared between them.

00:16:30.860 --> 00:16:33.560
But at other points,
and unfortunately,

00:16:33.560 --> 00:16:38.900
more and more in the past
few years, the demography

00:16:38.900 --> 00:16:41.150
of the Palestinians
and of the Israelis

00:16:41.150 --> 00:16:43.880
has changed to such
an extent that it's

00:16:43.880 --> 00:16:47.960
become far harder
on our side to look

00:16:47.960 --> 00:16:53.090
at the other party as people
with whom we can share

00:16:53.090 --> 00:16:58.400
and for the other side to look
upon us as a party with whom

00:16:58.400 --> 00:16:59.840
they can share.

00:16:59.840 --> 00:17:01.700
Of course, it's
far more difficult

00:17:01.700 --> 00:17:04.010
if you're thinking
of the sharing

00:17:04.010 --> 00:17:06.980
when it's being done
between parties.

00:17:06.980 --> 00:17:09.560
Then when it's being
done between individuals,

00:17:09.560 --> 00:17:13.460
individuals can get along with
one another far more easily.

00:17:13.460 --> 00:17:16.130
But when you're thinking
of the claimants

00:17:16.130 --> 00:17:18.560
to Jerusalem, Israelis
and Palestinians,

00:17:18.560 --> 00:17:22.130
and when you think of the
way that both sides, Israelis

00:17:22.130 --> 00:17:25.010
and Palestinians, have
actually transformed

00:17:25.010 --> 00:17:28.430
over the past few years,
transformed to the worse,

00:17:28.430 --> 00:17:38.540
transformed in a way that makes
each side begin to think more

00:17:38.540 --> 00:17:42.530
specifically, of themselves
and to exclude the other,

00:17:42.530 --> 00:17:45.290
it sort of has become
really a very hard business

00:17:45.290 --> 00:17:49.010
to try and see how
sharing can be done.

00:17:49.010 --> 00:17:52.830
I still hope that the
miracle will occur.

00:17:52.830 --> 00:17:54.890
I always hope that the
miracle will occur.

00:17:54.890 --> 00:18:00.800
After all, this is the Holy Land
and one should never lose hope.

00:18:00.800 --> 00:18:03.810
And I'm sure
something will occur.

00:18:03.810 --> 00:18:06.830
But if you look at things,
objectively, rationally,

00:18:06.830 --> 00:18:08.600
unfortunately--

00:18:08.600 --> 00:18:10.820
I see that the
situation has been

00:18:10.820 --> 00:18:14.360
deteriorating over
the past few years,

00:18:14.360 --> 00:18:16.370
over the past 10, 15 years.

00:18:16.370 --> 00:18:20.270
And I see that it's going to
be much harder to try and do

00:18:20.270 --> 00:18:21.710
something about it now.

00:18:21.710 --> 00:18:23.870
Recently, you all heard--

00:18:23.870 --> 00:18:27.020
I don't know how
Trump sounds here--

00:18:27.020 --> 00:18:28.798
how does he sound here, Trump?

00:18:28.798 --> 00:18:29.654
[AUDIENCE MURMURING]

00:18:29.654 --> 00:18:30.750
[LAUGHTER]

00:18:30.750 --> 00:18:31.250
OK.

00:18:34.380 --> 00:18:37.980
But you know I'm
mentioning him because,

00:18:37.980 --> 00:18:41.670
referring to what
[INAUDIBLE] said just now,

00:18:41.670 --> 00:18:45.810
that sometimes you
have to try and see

00:18:45.810 --> 00:18:49.080
beyond the immediate parameters.

00:18:49.080 --> 00:18:53.580
And what's been happening
over the past year

00:18:53.580 --> 00:18:58.330
with us is that the United
States policy, if you like,

00:18:58.330 --> 00:19:04.480
Trump policy, has been trying
to make us back home to see

00:19:04.480 --> 00:19:08.350
beyond the existing parameters,
beyond the existing parameters

00:19:08.350 --> 00:19:12.850
that we've actually been
living with for the past 15

00:19:12.850 --> 00:19:14.140
years of negotiations.

00:19:14.140 --> 00:19:14.920
Hydro?

00:19:14.920 --> 00:19:16.870
How are you?

00:19:16.870 --> 00:19:19.600
I understand it's
affirmative action somewhere.

00:19:19.600 --> 00:19:21.508
[LAUGHS]

00:19:26.590 --> 00:19:29.640
So you know, that's the
kind of thing that might--

00:19:29.640 --> 00:19:32.605
How is Trump making you
see beyond the parameters?

00:19:32.605 --> 00:19:33.210
He sees.

00:19:33.210 --> 00:19:33.710
No.

00:19:33.710 --> 00:19:37.050
But what about you,
when you hear about--

00:19:37.050 --> 00:19:37.600
OK.

00:19:37.600 --> 00:19:37.960
OK.

00:19:37.960 --> 00:19:38.530
That's good.

00:19:38.530 --> 00:19:39.940
Thank you for asking me.

00:19:42.520 --> 00:19:45.920
So I'm better when
I'm asked questions.

00:19:45.920 --> 00:19:47.650
So please ask questions.

00:19:47.650 --> 00:19:51.640
Now of course, we on
the Palestinian side

00:19:51.640 --> 00:19:54.340
are really very
angry with Trump.

00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:59.560
Because we've been sort of led
to believe over the past 10, 20

00:19:59.560 --> 00:20:03.010
years, through the Oslo
process before that,

00:20:03.010 --> 00:20:07.630
that we'll end up basically
having a state along the '67

00:20:07.630 --> 00:20:10.750
lines, East Jerusalem
as its capital,

00:20:10.750 --> 00:20:13.360
the refugee problem will
be resolved in the context

00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:15.190
of the Palestinian state.

00:20:15.190 --> 00:20:16.710
In general, that was the--

00:20:16.710 --> 00:20:18.720
and this has failed.

00:20:18.720 --> 00:20:21.620
Now Trump came along, or
comes along, and says,

00:20:21.620 --> 00:20:23.350
forget about that.

00:20:23.350 --> 00:20:25.120
Maybe you can think
about two states.

00:20:25.120 --> 00:20:27.370
But look at the wider region.

00:20:27.370 --> 00:20:30.700
Look at the world
around you and think

00:20:30.700 --> 00:20:35.140
about how this part of
the geography of the map

00:20:35.140 --> 00:20:38.260
can be linked up with
that, how people from here

00:20:38.260 --> 00:20:42.850
can be sort of linked up
with people from there.

00:20:42.850 --> 00:20:46.780
And it sort of makes one
think of a future beyond

00:20:46.780 --> 00:20:51.550
or a geography, if you
like, or a political area

00:20:51.550 --> 00:20:57.400
beyond the classical two
state solution or paradigm

00:20:57.400 --> 00:20:58.810
that we've been thinking of.

00:20:58.810 --> 00:21:01.090
Now I'm not saying
this is a good thing.

00:21:01.090 --> 00:21:05.600
And indeed, I mean, we look
upon it as a terrible thing,

00:21:05.600 --> 00:21:07.810
as Palestinians.

00:21:07.810 --> 00:21:11.710
But I'm saying
that maybe one does

00:21:11.710 --> 00:21:14.950
have to look beyond
existing parameters.

00:21:14.950 --> 00:21:16.510
I mean, at one point--

00:21:16.510 --> 00:21:18.670
I don't know if you
realize this or not--

00:21:18.670 --> 00:21:22.930
but what today-- for most
of us, for a lot of us--

00:21:22.930 --> 00:21:27.850
seems to be a very sort
of classical solution

00:21:27.850 --> 00:21:30.340
and rational solution,
which is a two state

00:21:30.340 --> 00:21:35.890
solution, at one point, believe
it or not, was totally crazy.

00:21:35.890 --> 00:21:38.410
It wasn't accepted at all.

00:21:38.410 --> 00:21:43.180
It took many years after '67, in
particular, it took many years

00:21:43.180 --> 00:21:44.960
until the Americans
came on board,

00:21:44.960 --> 00:21:48.280
the Europeans came on board,
everybody came on board

00:21:48.280 --> 00:21:51.040
for a two state solution.

00:21:51.040 --> 00:21:53.950
And it was a lot of hard
work to get everybody

00:21:53.950 --> 00:21:56.390
to accept a two state solution.

00:21:56.390 --> 00:22:01.750
So now to think or to propose
that a two state classical

00:22:01.750 --> 00:22:04.330
solution isn't
necessarily going to work,

00:22:04.330 --> 00:22:07.660
but other things might work--

00:22:07.660 --> 00:22:12.670
Can you just tell us a little
more about the Trump proposals?

00:22:12.670 --> 00:22:15.190
What are the Jew
territorial ideas?

00:22:15.190 --> 00:22:17.030
I mean, what will happen?

00:22:17.030 --> 00:22:19.720
I don't really know anything
about, I mean, you know,

00:22:19.720 --> 00:22:20.710
the Trump proposals.

00:22:20.710 --> 00:22:24.410
But what I gather is
that he's trying to bring

00:22:24.410 --> 00:22:26.680
in the rest of the Arab world.

00:22:26.680 --> 00:22:32.830
And he is basically trying to
go along with an Israeli, also,

00:22:32.830 --> 00:22:35.260
policy of trying
to what they call

00:22:35.260 --> 00:22:38.170
normalize relationships
between Israel

00:22:38.170 --> 00:22:42.310
and the Arab world as a
prelude, or as a condition for,

00:22:42.310 --> 00:22:48.610
going ahead with developing,
giving more leeway

00:22:48.610 --> 00:22:50.200
for the Palestinians.

00:22:50.200 --> 00:22:52.900
Now I don't know how
far they want to go

00:22:52.900 --> 00:22:54.760
in terms of giving a leeway.

00:22:54.760 --> 00:22:57.520
I don't know how far Trump
has in mind or anybody

00:22:57.520 --> 00:22:59.920
has in mind for the
Palestinians-- do

00:22:59.920 --> 00:23:04.930
they want us to have a state
or not, properly speaking.

00:23:04.930 --> 00:23:09.320
But I think they're trying to
think of the entire region,

00:23:09.320 --> 00:23:11.180
so to speak.

00:23:11.180 --> 00:23:16.720
They have many ideas of
linking up the region.

00:23:16.720 --> 00:23:20.740
For instance, the minister
of transport in Israel

00:23:20.740 --> 00:23:25.750
apparently has very daring
ideas about railway tracks that

00:23:25.750 --> 00:23:28.580
will bring everybody together.

00:23:28.580 --> 00:23:32.500
There was a visit recently
of Netanyahu to Muscat,

00:23:32.500 --> 00:23:38.080
in which the sultan
of Oman was basically

00:23:38.080 --> 00:23:42.670
welcoming this kind of new
world order, if you like,

00:23:42.670 --> 00:23:44.260
or regional order.

00:23:44.260 --> 00:23:46.760
Now I don't know where we
will end up as Palestinians.

00:23:46.760 --> 00:23:48.240
Maybe we will ask--

00:23:48.240 --> 00:23:49.030
Diaspora.

00:23:49.030 --> 00:23:51.430
--yes, it's possible, diaspora.

00:23:51.430 --> 00:23:55.030
But also it's possible
that we will end up

00:23:55.030 --> 00:23:57.730
in a single system
with Israelis.

00:23:57.730 --> 00:24:02.410
In other words, by default
again, in one state.

00:24:02.410 --> 00:24:05.050
Now I'm not sure whether
immediately people

00:24:05.050 --> 00:24:08.910
will be able to achieve
full rights in such a state.

00:24:08.910 --> 00:24:13.300
Certainly, it doesn't look
like this way for now.

00:24:13.300 --> 00:24:15.590
But eventually, maybe,
that's what will happen.

00:24:15.590 --> 00:24:19.510
I mean, if you look ahead,
not 10 or 20 or 30 years,

00:24:19.510 --> 00:24:22.211
but further ahead, maybe
that's what will happen.

00:24:22.211 --> 00:24:23.710
Maybe that's the
only thing that can

00:24:23.710 --> 00:24:27.370
happen to get the Israelis
and the Palestinians somehow,

00:24:27.370 --> 00:24:31.240
who are living in that
area, to in fact share

00:24:31.240 --> 00:24:33.790
the entire political system.

00:24:33.790 --> 00:24:37.360
A lot has to be transformed in
the psychologies and attitudes

00:24:37.360 --> 00:24:40.270
and creeds and beliefs of
the people, the Palestinians

00:24:40.270 --> 00:24:41.590
and Israelis.

00:24:41.590 --> 00:24:45.010
But maybe that's the
only way to go forward.

00:24:45.010 --> 00:24:46.860
So you've finished?

00:24:46.860 --> 00:24:48.360
Do you want me to
ask you questions?

00:24:48.360 --> 00:24:49.050
How do you want to play this?

00:24:49.050 --> 00:24:49.590
I think--

00:24:49.590 --> 00:24:51.570
I should stop
myself from talking.

00:24:51.570 --> 00:24:53.240
Well, let me ask you this then.

00:24:53.240 --> 00:24:59.340
Well, two things-- one,
if you look back 40 years

00:24:59.340 --> 00:25:02.460
and you now look at
the situation now,

00:25:02.460 --> 00:25:04.480
think of what you had.

00:25:04.480 --> 00:25:06.720
You know, the hopes
you'd had, the

00:25:06.720 --> 00:25:10.530
plans you'd had for the region,
and now think of where you are.

00:25:13.809 --> 00:25:14.850
How do you feel about it?

00:25:19.030 --> 00:25:21.680
In one word, very sad--

00:25:21.680 --> 00:25:24.440
I think it's very
sad because I think

00:25:24.440 --> 00:25:29.660
that we've been paying a
high price, both Israelis

00:25:29.660 --> 00:25:32.990
and Palestinians,
certainly Palestinians.

00:25:32.990 --> 00:25:37.580
And to my mind, you
know, paying a price

00:25:37.580 --> 00:25:42.330
that we needn't have paid
in some way or another.

00:25:42.330 --> 00:25:45.020
I think that maybe we--

00:25:45.020 --> 00:25:47.480
in some mysterious way
we need to have paid it.

00:25:47.480 --> 00:25:50.270
But when you look
at it rationally,

00:25:50.270 --> 00:25:54.271
you don't think that
it was necessary.

00:25:54.271 --> 00:25:54.770
Look.

00:25:54.770 --> 00:25:58.280
I mean, I started
out many years ago.

00:25:58.280 --> 00:26:02.540
The first time I actually
accepted a two state solution

00:26:02.540 --> 00:26:07.190
was, believe it or not, when I
was a student here at Harvard.

00:26:07.190 --> 00:26:09.830
And someone came--

00:26:09.830 --> 00:26:13.190
Professor [INAUDIBLE]
came to visit.

00:26:13.190 --> 00:26:16.010
And he gave us a talk, the
Palestinian, Arab student

00:26:16.010 --> 00:26:19.340
community here, about
a two state solution.

00:26:19.340 --> 00:26:22.280
And I remember feeling
very angry with that.

00:26:22.280 --> 00:26:27.530
Because at the time, my idea was
why should there be two states?

00:26:27.530 --> 00:26:30.110
You know, can't we
all live in one state?

00:26:30.110 --> 00:26:34.590
And can't we all have equal
rights, and so on and so forth.

00:26:34.590 --> 00:26:37.460
But then slowly, that was in--

00:26:37.460 --> 00:26:42.830
when was it, in '74 maybe,
or thereabouts, or '75.

00:26:42.830 --> 00:26:45.020
And then I went back home.

00:26:45.020 --> 00:26:48.110
I started teaching at Birzeit.

00:26:48.110 --> 00:26:52.200
And I started learning
from the students

00:26:52.200 --> 00:26:58.460
I was teaching about the real
needs, as opposed to the ideas

00:26:58.460 --> 00:27:00.500
that I had in my head.

00:27:00.500 --> 00:27:05.840
And I started seeing that
the students' real needs had

00:27:05.840 --> 00:27:10.910
to do with two
basic needs, which

00:27:10.910 --> 00:27:14.060
were freedom and independence,
to be independent

00:27:14.060 --> 00:27:14.780
and to be free.

00:27:14.780 --> 00:27:17.390
That's to say, to
have their own state.

00:27:17.390 --> 00:27:20.390
And therefore, I went
along, basically,

00:27:20.390 --> 00:27:23.570
with the idea of two
states on the basis

00:27:23.570 --> 00:27:27.740
that the students I was teaching
wanted a state of their own

00:27:27.740 --> 00:27:30.020
and were prepared
to have a two state

00:27:30.020 --> 00:27:32.060
solution alongside Israel.

00:27:32.060 --> 00:27:32.950
And that developed.

00:27:32.950 --> 00:27:36.260
And so I worked
very hard in order

00:27:36.260 --> 00:27:38.840
to try and bring that about.

00:27:38.840 --> 00:27:42.170
And as you know, I was
part of or involved

00:27:42.170 --> 00:27:48.020
in, whether second track
or indirect negotiations

00:27:48.020 --> 00:27:50.450
with Israelis for
many, many years

00:27:50.450 --> 00:27:54.230
trying to bring that solution
about, a two state solution.

00:27:54.230 --> 00:27:58.010
But unfortunately,
for different reasons,

00:27:58.010 --> 00:28:01.230
this hasn't come about.

00:28:01.230 --> 00:28:05.060
And I feel sad about this.

00:28:05.060 --> 00:28:07.490
And I feel that, in
many ways, maybe I

00:28:07.490 --> 00:28:10.850
was naive at the time to
think that a two state

00:28:10.850 --> 00:28:13.640
solution is indeed possible.

00:28:13.640 --> 00:28:18.750
And although I
reject, in my head,

00:28:18.750 --> 00:28:23.570
thinking about things
being inevitable and so on,

00:28:23.570 --> 00:28:26.750
but you know, I've begun to
think recently that maybe--

00:28:26.750 --> 00:28:29.690
maybe-- the idea
of Zionism is not

00:28:29.690 --> 00:28:32.750
something that, in fact, works.

00:28:32.750 --> 00:28:39.090
It isn't something that can
coexist with another party,

00:28:39.090 --> 00:28:41.360
with the Palestinians.

00:28:41.360 --> 00:28:43.580
It was at one point.

00:28:43.580 --> 00:28:46.290
It could exist, could have
existed, maybe, at one point.

00:28:46.290 --> 00:28:49.220
But I think there have
been transformations

00:28:49.220 --> 00:28:52.430
taking place within
Zionism, within the state

00:28:52.430 --> 00:28:54.020
ideology of Israel.

00:28:54.020 --> 00:28:56.990
As indeed, also,
unfortunately, there

00:28:56.990 --> 00:29:02.060
have been also transformations
on the Palestinian side,

00:29:02.060 --> 00:29:09.050
with the ideology on both sides
becoming less inclusive, less

00:29:09.050 --> 00:29:14.270
accepting of the other.

00:29:14.270 --> 00:29:17.450
So yeah, in one
[? state, ?] I feel sad.

00:29:17.450 --> 00:29:19.930
You know, we had David Grossman.

00:29:19.930 --> 00:29:21.710
I'd invited David Grossman here.

00:29:21.710 --> 00:29:25.820
And he gave a very effecting
and beautiful lecture.

00:29:25.820 --> 00:29:31.690
You know, his view
was very pessimistic.

00:29:31.690 --> 00:29:35.410
But he said that we live in
these different bubbles there.

00:29:35.410 --> 00:29:37.630
I mean, he was very
honest about it.

00:29:37.630 --> 00:29:39.610
We may share a
whole lot of things.

00:29:39.610 --> 00:29:41.740
He said within the
bubble in which I live,

00:29:41.740 --> 00:29:47.860
I can say whatever I feel like
about the Zionist, Israeli

00:29:47.860 --> 00:29:48.640
nation state.

00:29:48.640 --> 00:29:52.630
And he was very, very--
he's very critical.

00:29:52.630 --> 00:30:00.170
But when you talk, and even
he talked about both sides,

00:30:00.170 --> 00:30:03.410
and we talk about the
question of sharing,

00:30:03.410 --> 00:30:07.610
you talked about the analogy of
your children, that your son--

00:30:07.610 --> 00:30:09.140
what does it mean
to share an idea,

00:30:09.140 --> 00:30:13.460
or to share an orange, or
children, please share a cake?

00:30:13.460 --> 00:30:16.650
And as you said, there is
a sense of equality there.

00:30:16.650 --> 00:30:19.850
You know, you wouldn't say
that because you're a woman

00:30:19.850 --> 00:30:24.530
or you're a girl, you should
have a smaller slice of cake.

00:30:24.530 --> 00:30:27.110
But what is it--

00:30:27.110 --> 00:30:30.380
I mean, how are these
two sides disposed?

00:30:30.380 --> 00:30:33.110
Can we talk about
sharing as if people come

00:30:33.110 --> 00:30:35.789
to the table in the same way?

00:30:35.789 --> 00:30:36.830
What's the point of that?

00:30:36.830 --> 00:30:38.750
I mean, do they really
come in the same way,

00:30:38.750 --> 00:30:42.860
or are there profound
structural differences?

00:30:42.860 --> 00:30:47.900
If somebody comes to the
table hungry, really hungry,

00:30:47.900 --> 00:30:52.250
you know, they would see it as
a right to take 3/4 of the cake.

00:30:52.250 --> 00:30:57.860
The question of sharing,
then, is not some ideal order.

00:30:57.860 --> 00:30:59.900
It is a sense of need.

00:30:59.900 --> 00:31:06.870
It is a sense of psychic
desire, from trauma.

00:31:06.870 --> 00:31:11.090
So should we be
talking about this

00:31:11.090 --> 00:31:15.260
with all these [? negotiatory ?]
balances, two sides,

00:31:15.260 --> 00:31:18.580
or are we evading something?

00:31:18.580 --> 00:31:20.590
If I understand
you, I'm not sure--

00:31:20.590 --> 00:31:26.950
but I think that the two ways
of looking at this orange,

00:31:26.950 --> 00:31:31.860
in this case, looking
at Jerusalem, one way--

00:31:31.860 --> 00:31:34.870
and that has been the
classical approach--

00:31:34.870 --> 00:31:40.880
is to say Jerusalem has
Palestinians, has Israelis.

00:31:40.880 --> 00:31:43.960
A best way to approach the
problem of the conflict

00:31:43.960 --> 00:31:47.660
between them, the conflicting
claims between them

00:31:47.660 --> 00:31:50.290
is simply to divide it up--

00:31:50.290 --> 00:31:51.910
not share, but to divide.

00:31:51.910 --> 00:31:53.240
Divide it up.

00:31:53.240 --> 00:31:56.440
Divide it up between
one side, which is then

00:31:56.440 --> 00:31:58.990
run entirely by
the Palestinians,

00:31:58.990 --> 00:32:00.460
and the other by the Israelis.

00:32:00.460 --> 00:32:02.750
And this is the
classical approach.

00:32:02.750 --> 00:32:05.920
So here you're dividing,
you're not sharing, in a sense.

00:32:05.920 --> 00:32:08.240
And it's much
easier, much simpler.

00:32:08.240 --> 00:32:11.440
It's sort of taking the orange
in the middle, or some point,

00:32:11.440 --> 00:32:13.560
and cutting it in
half and saying, OK,

00:32:13.560 --> 00:32:16.180
you can do with your
piece what you want.

00:32:16.180 --> 00:32:18.520
And I'll do what I want.

00:32:18.520 --> 00:32:22.120
But this has become more
and more difficult to do,

00:32:22.120 --> 00:32:24.640
the actual geographic division.

00:32:24.640 --> 00:32:28.300
And so now people sometimes
say, well, maybe we

00:32:28.300 --> 00:32:30.530
can have a shared capital.

00:32:30.530 --> 00:32:35.140
So it's not a capital that can
be divided up geographically,

00:32:35.140 --> 00:32:37.300
but it can be shared.

00:32:37.300 --> 00:32:42.010
But the question is
how can this be shared?

00:32:42.010 --> 00:32:44.530
There has to be, as
you said earlier,

00:32:44.530 --> 00:32:52.060
for a proper sharing, some
kind of equitable recognition

00:32:52.060 --> 00:32:53.690
of the one by the other.

00:32:53.690 --> 00:32:55.240
Now by recognition,
what do I mean?

00:32:55.240 --> 00:32:58.540
I mean, respect for the
creed, for the religion,

00:32:58.540 --> 00:33:01.540
for the culture, for
the national memory,

00:33:01.540 --> 00:33:04.930
for the narrative, for all
kinds of things which it's

00:33:04.930 --> 00:33:08.440
very hard to do
now for the moment,

00:33:08.440 --> 00:33:12.100
which it's actually becoming
harder and harder to do.

00:33:12.100 --> 00:33:14.600
But that's the only
kind of sharing.

00:33:14.600 --> 00:33:22.210
Now it's possible to share, for
instance, services in the city.

00:33:22.210 --> 00:33:23.840
Even if it's somehow--

00:33:23.840 --> 00:33:28.420
with the kind of porous open
border, you can share services.

00:33:28.420 --> 00:33:32.120
You can share a lot of public
services, most of them,

00:33:32.120 --> 00:33:32.620
perhaps.

00:33:32.620 --> 00:33:34.840
You can share lots
of things and still

00:33:34.840 --> 00:33:38.860
maintain some kind of
equitable geographic balance,

00:33:38.860 --> 00:33:44.530
demographic balance on
one side and the other.

00:33:44.530 --> 00:33:46.310
I mean, things are possible.

00:33:46.310 --> 00:33:52.540
But I'm not sure that people are
up to, now, talking about this

00:33:52.540 --> 00:33:54.550
or reaching solutions about it.

00:33:54.550 --> 00:33:57.040
When we talk about
sharing, there's

00:33:57.040 --> 00:34:01.610
also some kind of sense
of openness of the object.

00:34:01.610 --> 00:34:05.260
Now without talking about the
Palestinians or the Israelis

00:34:05.260 --> 00:34:10.330
for a minute, the whole
security apparatus

00:34:10.330 --> 00:34:14.889
is such that the question
of exchange or passing

00:34:14.889 --> 00:34:19.840
is so difficult, with the
barriers, the surveillance,

00:34:19.840 --> 00:34:21.929
the wall that skirts--

00:34:21.929 --> 00:34:24.949
you know, that divides
people's lands--

00:34:24.949 --> 00:34:32.050
the settlements that are a
continual imperial outrage.

00:34:32.050 --> 00:34:40.929
So it seems to me that,
Sari, I applaud your sense

00:34:40.929 --> 00:34:47.949
that maybe 40 years from now or
a half, something will happen.

00:34:47.949 --> 00:34:50.025
But from everything
you have said--

00:34:50.025 --> 00:34:50.650
Something good.

00:34:50.650 --> 00:34:51.858
--something good will happen.

00:34:51.858 --> 00:34:54.820
But from everything you've
said over the past 40 years,

00:34:54.820 --> 00:35:00.130
and indeed, the
trough now, it seems

00:35:00.130 --> 00:35:01.870
very difficult to imagine.

00:35:01.870 --> 00:35:06.700
So what is this
dream of progress?

00:35:06.700 --> 00:35:08.660
Of course, one has
to live that dream.

00:35:08.660 --> 00:35:16.510
But are there small instances
of the local state or local

00:35:16.510 --> 00:35:18.130
initiatives that
would give us hope?

00:35:18.130 --> 00:35:21.070
Because what you just said
about today's election,

00:35:21.070 --> 00:35:25.720
where less than
1% of Palestinians

00:35:25.720 --> 00:35:28.070
are represented
in the municipal--

00:35:28.070 --> 00:35:28.825
Participating.

00:35:28.825 --> 00:35:30.700
--or participated in
the municipal election--

00:35:30.700 --> 00:35:32.990
I mean, that's,
like, a disaster.

00:35:32.990 --> 00:35:36.840
And people do say-- by the
way, I was in Germany recently

00:35:36.840 --> 00:35:38.800
and the people from Haifa--

00:35:38.800 --> 00:35:43.810
people do say that there is some
sense in Haifa of there being,

00:35:43.810 --> 00:35:49.000
at least at the level
of the civil society,

00:35:49.000 --> 00:35:54.880
groups that meet with
some element of equality

00:35:54.880 --> 00:35:56.260
in their discussions of that.

00:35:56.260 --> 00:35:57.540
I'm sure that happens
in [INAUDIBLE]..

00:35:57.540 --> 00:35:58.900
I'm sure it happens in Tel Aviv.

00:35:58.900 --> 00:36:02.790
But none of it seems to
impact on the structure.

00:36:02.790 --> 00:36:03.290
Yeah.

00:36:07.450 --> 00:36:08.904
I was talking about--

00:36:08.904 --> 00:36:11.320
if you like, when I was talking
about sharing and dividing

00:36:11.320 --> 00:36:14.200
and so on in the context
of Jerusalem, of course,

00:36:14.200 --> 00:36:17.260
I was not taking into account
the rest of the West Bank,

00:36:17.260 --> 00:36:21.050
and even more, the
West Bank, Gaza

00:36:21.050 --> 00:36:23.940
kind of geographic situation.

00:36:23.940 --> 00:36:27.639
And of course, in the context
of the present situation,

00:36:27.639 --> 00:36:29.180
you can't really
talk about anything.

00:36:29.180 --> 00:36:33.560
I mean, there's nothing
really to discuss seriously,

00:36:33.560 --> 00:36:35.480
positively, in a
positive fashion.

00:36:35.480 --> 00:36:38.570
But what I was trying to
say was that, in a better

00:36:38.570 --> 00:36:43.070
kind of situation, in a
better kind of climate,

00:36:43.070 --> 00:36:46.340
it is still possible to address
the different issues that we

00:36:46.340 --> 00:36:47.240
have.

00:36:47.240 --> 00:36:50.810
It is mathematically possible
to adjust the different issues

00:36:50.810 --> 00:36:52.610
that we have, whether
it's in the West

00:36:52.610 --> 00:36:55.100
Bank or Gaza or Jerusalem.

00:36:55.100 --> 00:37:00.920
The problem is not that it is in
itself, logically, if you like,

00:37:00.920 --> 00:37:02.510
a puzzle that cannot be solved.

00:37:02.510 --> 00:37:06.697
It is something
that is political.

00:37:06.697 --> 00:37:08.030
And that is the problem with it.

00:37:11.560 --> 00:37:15.030
It is what poses a problem
politically, but not logically,

00:37:15.030 --> 00:37:15.530
I think.

00:37:15.530 --> 00:37:19.430
So if the climate is changed,
and that is possible.

00:37:19.430 --> 00:37:23.060
And what makes it possible
is what you just said.

00:37:23.060 --> 00:37:26.850
That if you go beyond
the surface a little bit,

00:37:26.850 --> 00:37:30.320
if you look at society, if you
look at individuals and so on,

00:37:30.320 --> 00:37:33.290
you'll find that actually
people, at the end of the day,

00:37:33.290 --> 00:37:34.820
are human beings.

00:37:34.820 --> 00:37:36.500
And they often, at
different levels,

00:37:36.500 --> 00:37:40.440
interact with one another as
equals and as human beings.

00:37:40.440 --> 00:37:45.080
It is only when
they take on, they

00:37:45.080 --> 00:37:49.040
put on the cloak of politics
in one situation or another

00:37:49.040 --> 00:37:52.670
that then there is
a different dynamic.

00:37:52.670 --> 00:37:57.830
But underneath, I think, there
are many cases, I believe,

00:37:57.830 --> 00:38:02.480
of people really
believing that they

00:38:02.480 --> 00:38:06.320
are equal to the other side.

00:38:06.320 --> 00:38:07.571
I can't think of examples now.

00:38:07.571 --> 00:38:08.070
But--

00:38:08.070 --> 00:38:08.670
[LAUGHTER]

00:38:08.670 --> 00:38:11.240
Sari, if I might say--

00:38:11.240 --> 00:38:12.920
I'll give you an example.

00:38:12.920 --> 00:38:14.730
I'll give you an example.

00:38:14.730 --> 00:38:19.640
So one good example,
I think, is this--

00:38:19.640 --> 00:38:26.630
the Youth Orchestra of
Israeli and Palestinians.

00:38:26.630 --> 00:38:34.100
And which gave me once the idea
of writing something to talk.

00:38:34.100 --> 00:38:38.170
And this was a talk--

00:38:38.170 --> 00:38:42.590
the context was
something called sound,

00:38:42.590 --> 00:38:45.980
or sound and identity,
or space and identity.

00:38:45.980 --> 00:38:48.660
And I wasn't sure what
to say in this context.

00:38:48.660 --> 00:38:50.480
That's the conference
I was invited

00:38:50.480 --> 00:38:52.700
to speak or give a talk at.

00:38:52.700 --> 00:38:56.470
And I was sitting with
Lucy, with my wife,

00:38:56.470 --> 00:39:03.050
at the place where there was
a Youth Orchestra, Israelis

00:39:03.050 --> 00:39:03.860
and Palestinians.

00:39:03.860 --> 00:39:06.930
They were about 14,
15, 16 years old.

00:39:06.930 --> 00:39:09.320
And they were practicing
singing together.

00:39:09.320 --> 00:39:10.790
And they were singing.

00:39:10.790 --> 00:39:13.040
And they sang a beautiful song.

00:39:13.040 --> 00:39:15.210
You can actually Google it.

00:39:15.210 --> 00:39:16.940
They sang a beautiful
song called, "I

00:39:16.940 --> 00:39:18.470
Want to Make This Your Home."

00:39:18.470 --> 00:39:20.630
"I Want to Make This Your Home."

00:39:20.630 --> 00:39:24.960
Now this is an Israeli
and a Palestinian--

00:39:24.960 --> 00:39:27.470
not just, you know,
there were 10 of them.

00:39:27.470 --> 00:39:34.640
And I liked I liked the title,
that I want to make this home.

00:39:34.640 --> 00:39:38.120
I liked it being
sung by the Israeli,

00:39:38.120 --> 00:39:42.440
addressed, as I imagined,
to the Palestinian.

00:39:42.440 --> 00:39:46.130
And I liked it being sung by the
Palestinian, as I imagined it,

00:39:46.130 --> 00:39:47.390
being sung to the Israeli.

00:39:47.390 --> 00:39:50.450
And they were singing
it in Arabic, in Hebrew,

00:39:50.450 --> 00:39:51.710
and in English.

00:39:51.710 --> 00:39:55.800
And I said to myself,
you know, this is great.

00:39:55.800 --> 00:39:57.650
This is a new sound.

00:39:57.650 --> 00:39:59.660
And this is a sound
that is creating

00:39:59.660 --> 00:40:04.670
a new space of identity,
an identity of sharing.

00:40:04.670 --> 00:40:08.870
And I went home, and I worked
a lot about this, on this,

00:40:08.870 --> 00:40:12.580
and developed a whole
sort of concept.

00:40:12.580 --> 00:40:14.990
And went very happily
to give a talk,

00:40:14.990 --> 00:40:18.440
and actually brought
together with me

00:40:18.440 --> 00:40:21.920
to that talk the orchestra--

00:40:21.920 --> 00:40:23.010
what you call them-- the--

00:40:23.010 --> 00:40:23.510
Choir?

00:40:23.510 --> 00:40:24.270
[INAUDIBLE]

00:40:24.270 --> 00:40:26.070
Was it a choir?

00:40:26.070 --> 00:40:26.810
It was a choir.

00:40:26.810 --> 00:40:27.860
No, we showed it on--

00:40:27.860 --> 00:40:29.930
because it was in
Hawaii, the conference--

00:40:29.930 --> 00:40:34.010
I couldn't take
with me to Hawaii.

00:40:34.010 --> 00:40:37.610
But he came, not
the entire group.

00:40:37.610 --> 00:40:40.950
But it made me feel good.

00:40:40.950 --> 00:40:42.240
It still does.

00:40:42.240 --> 00:40:45.020
And I think you'll
find many examples

00:40:45.020 --> 00:40:48.290
like this, which gives us
hope, which gives one hope,

00:40:48.290 --> 00:40:49.580
gives me hope.

00:40:49.580 --> 00:40:53.390
It is saddening, yes, that
it's taking us so long,

00:40:53.390 --> 00:40:56.900
that it's taking so much time.

00:40:56.900 --> 00:41:00.320
It is saddening especially
for me as a Palestinian.

00:41:00.320 --> 00:41:04.550
Because as you probably know,
the pressure on this side,

00:41:04.550 --> 00:41:09.200
on the Palestinian side,
is far, far, far greater

00:41:09.200 --> 00:41:10.810
than it is on the Israeli side.

00:41:10.810 --> 00:41:14.870
We are sort of at the
receiving end, if you like.

00:41:14.870 --> 00:41:17.000
We live in constant anxiety.

00:41:17.000 --> 00:41:19.270
We live in constant--

00:41:19.270 --> 00:41:20.110
I don't know if--

00:41:20.110 --> 00:41:26.920
I don't know myself, even, if I
am sort of fully normal by now

00:41:26.920 --> 00:41:30.280
as a result of the pressures
that we live under.

00:41:33.270 --> 00:41:36.190
But even so, my
hope still exists.

00:41:36.190 --> 00:41:39.490
And I think we should
all continue to hope.

00:41:39.490 --> 00:41:42.190
And I think if we all
hope, then you know,

00:41:42.190 --> 00:41:43.490
we all can do something.

00:41:43.490 --> 00:41:45.060
Let me ask you
one last question.

00:41:45.060 --> 00:41:45.925
Then I want to show
the photographs.

00:41:45.925 --> 00:41:47.940
And I want you to
just respond to them.

00:41:47.940 --> 00:41:48.640
OK.

00:41:48.640 --> 00:41:53.080
So you said a moment ago
that if things change--

00:41:53.080 --> 00:41:54.770
and this is a very
big question--

00:41:54.770 --> 00:41:56.740
I don't know what should change.

00:41:56.740 --> 00:42:00.640
Should it change within
the Palestinians?

00:42:00.640 --> 00:42:04.810
Which parties there, which
governmental structure

00:42:04.810 --> 00:42:07.990
should change-- this we can
have a conversation about.

00:42:07.990 --> 00:42:15.280
But I want to put the whole
issue, the Middle East issue

00:42:15.280 --> 00:42:19.720
in the more general context,
in the context of Saudi Arabia.

00:42:19.720 --> 00:42:23.140
In the context of the
United States where,

00:42:23.140 --> 00:42:28.150
of course, from what you
say, Trump is very happy

00:42:28.150 --> 00:42:33.220
trying to rethink a kind of
a federation of Palestinians.

00:42:33.220 --> 00:42:36.340
Whereas here, you know,
Mexicans are not allowed--

00:42:36.340 --> 00:42:37.380
children [INAUDIBLE].

00:42:37.380 --> 00:42:39.520
I mean, so I just
consider that to be

00:42:39.520 --> 00:42:44.230
a hideous way of displacing
what is on his doorstep.

00:42:44.230 --> 00:42:46.360
But then you have Turkey.

00:42:46.360 --> 00:42:49.400
You have the
problems in Lebanon,

00:42:49.400 --> 00:42:53.260
where there are a
number of Palestinians.

00:42:53.260 --> 00:42:56.630
But generally, this kind of--

00:42:56.630 --> 00:42:59.930
Hannah Arendt called
tribal nationalism,

00:42:59.930 --> 00:43:05.170
nationalism where the
leaders of the country

00:43:05.170 --> 00:43:07.120
set themselves up as saviors.

00:43:07.120 --> 00:43:10.180
I mean, Netanyahu does
this the whole time

00:43:10.180 --> 00:43:12.160
with Trump's encouragement.

00:43:12.160 --> 00:43:14.440
The enemy is not--

00:43:14.440 --> 00:43:16.130
that they are the enemy, really.

00:43:16.130 --> 00:43:16.880
They're the enemy.

00:43:16.880 --> 00:43:19.640
The majority is
the real minority.

00:43:19.640 --> 00:43:23.560
And they need to recover
everything that they've lost.

00:43:23.560 --> 00:43:27.430
So with that kind
of world scenario,

00:43:27.430 --> 00:43:32.100
how is it specifically affecting
the claims of the Palestinians

00:43:32.100 --> 00:43:32.700
now?

00:43:32.700 --> 00:43:33.199
Now?

00:43:35.590 --> 00:43:37.990
You ask a very hard question.

00:43:37.990 --> 00:43:41.020
I think-- let me tell you.

00:43:41.020 --> 00:43:44.170
I mean, the Palestinians
have actually

00:43:44.170 --> 00:43:51.100
been living in a state of
chaos in the past 10 years,

00:43:51.100 --> 00:43:53.850
especially since the
death of Arafat, I think,

00:43:53.850 --> 00:43:56.790
and with the lack of progress.

00:43:56.790 --> 00:44:01.510
And in particular, in
the past few days--

00:44:01.510 --> 00:44:03.270
you may have heard or
not, I'm not sure--

00:44:03.270 --> 00:44:08.220
but there's been problems with
the actual structure, the PLO

00:44:08.220 --> 00:44:11.400
structure that we've had for,
as [? our ?] representative

00:44:11.400 --> 00:44:13.180
for many years.

00:44:13.180 --> 00:44:19.440
But in the meantime, for some
reason, and somehow or another,

00:44:19.440 --> 00:44:22.110
the Palestinians have
actually been able,

00:44:22.110 --> 00:44:28.530
are able, are managing, to
bring themselves together again.

00:44:28.530 --> 00:44:33.390
And so, for example, I was
contacted at one point a few

00:44:33.390 --> 00:44:37.070
months ago by somebody
who came and said--

00:44:37.070 --> 00:44:38.460
and two and three people--

00:44:38.460 --> 00:44:41.860
to me, look, something is
wrong with the structure.

00:44:41.860 --> 00:44:44.250
These are academics,
journalists, Palestinians,

00:44:44.250 --> 00:44:47.160
one living in Turkey, one
living I don't know where.

00:44:47.160 --> 00:44:50.940
But they came and said--
and one Israeli Palestinian.

00:44:50.940 --> 00:44:55.530
And we should get together
and try and think again

00:44:55.530 --> 00:44:58.660
of what we should be doing.

00:44:58.660 --> 00:45:02.310
And so we started the whole
movement, if you like,

00:45:02.310 --> 00:45:05.730
of Palestinians, Palestinians
that come from the refugee

00:45:05.730 --> 00:45:08.820
camps in Syria,
Palestinians that

