00:51:35.630 --> 00:51:36.890
temple, for instance--

00:51:36.890 --> 00:51:38.290
Jewish temple.

00:51:38.290 --> 00:51:39.560
They did not destroy anything.

00:51:39.560 --> 00:51:41.740
It was a totally what's it.

00:51:41.740 --> 00:51:46.250
And so 500 years later, they
came and built something.

00:51:46.250 --> 00:51:49.400
It wasn't-- and in many
ways, they built it,

00:51:49.400 --> 00:51:55.070
in my own opinion, as a way of
commemorating the existence--

00:51:55.070 --> 00:51:58.370
but this is not a very
popular thing for me to say--

00:51:58.370 --> 00:52:01.530
the existence of the temple.

00:52:01.530 --> 00:52:04.420
In my opinion, this was
the whole idea behind it,

00:52:04.420 --> 00:52:07.860
that this was an
affirmation of a continuity

00:52:07.860 --> 00:52:10.680
of the Abrahamic religions.

00:52:10.680 --> 00:52:15.510
That's why it was built. It was
not to deny the Jewish history.

00:52:15.510 --> 00:52:18.750
It was to reaffirm
it, in many ways.

00:52:18.750 --> 00:52:21.110
And this is, again,
what makes it sad.

00:52:21.110 --> 00:52:24.870
That now it's the point
over which there is

00:52:24.870 --> 00:52:27.690
