00:59:57.170 --> 00:59:58.120
I'm the dark side.

00:59:58.120 --> 00:59:59.120
Melissa's the dark side.

00:59:59.120 --> 01:00:02.600
Just because, given the
constellation of world leaders

01:00:02.600 --> 01:00:07.115
we have right now, anything
bad can happen and does.

01:00:09.830 --> 01:00:13.340
So from a different
perspective, two questions--

01:00:13.340 --> 01:00:15.090
what's the worst
thing that can happen?

01:00:15.090 --> 01:00:17.240
What would be the worst
move that would destroy

01:00:17.240 --> 01:00:20.180
any possibility of peace?

01:00:20.180 --> 01:00:24.840
And what would be,
on the not dark side,

01:00:24.840 --> 01:00:27.650
what would be a situation
where the Palestinians

01:00:27.650 --> 01:00:32.130
and the Israelis had to work
together just to survive?

01:00:32.130 --> 01:00:38.120
So what can you imagine
bringing them together?

01:00:38.120 --> 01:00:40.650
Like a crisis, climate change--

01:00:40.650 --> 01:00:42.069
I don't know, something.

01:00:42.069 --> 01:00:44.360
And then what could you
imagine is the worst thing that

01:00:44.360 --> 01:00:49.260
could happen, for instance,
Trump and Netanyahu could do,

01:00:49.260 --> 01:00:50.780
and what are the other guys--

01:00:50.780 --> 01:00:53.500
the Saudi?

01:00:53.500 --> 01:00:56.464
I don't think Trump and
Netanyahu can do things--

01:00:56.464 --> 01:00:57.130
I mean, as such.

01:00:57.130 --> 01:01:00.250
But what can happen
the worst thing

01:01:00.250 --> 01:01:06.250
is a series of tragic
accidents or incidents, one

01:01:06.250 --> 01:01:17.350
leading to the other, and ending
up with, maybe, a major effort

01:01:17.350 --> 01:01:19.570
to expel Palestinians.

01:01:19.570 --> 01:01:24.650
So sort of one act
leading to another,

01:01:24.650 --> 01:01:27.940
becoming more explosive
and leading to eviction,

01:01:27.940 --> 01:01:30.010
mass eviction of people.

01:01:30.010 --> 01:01:32.930
And that would be
a terrible thing,

01:01:32.930 --> 01:01:38.970
I think, a worse thing
for a long period of time.

01:01:42.200 --> 01:01:48.650
And what can happen is if the
Palestinians and the Israelis

01:01:48.650 --> 01:01:54.680
get together, is
if suddenly we see

01:01:54.680 --> 01:02:01.430
Netanyahu attended by a lot of
right wing religious leaders

01:02:01.430 --> 01:02:08.180
hugging up Hamas with leaders
and Muslim religious extremist

01:02:08.180 --> 01:02:09.150
leaders.

01:02:09.150 --> 01:02:11.060
I think if that
happens and people

01:02:11.060 --> 01:02:15.315
see that, I think people
will come together again.

01:02:15.315 --> 01:02:17.850
Sari, there's this
gentleman in green.

01:02:17.850 --> 01:02:18.726
Could you-- oh, yeah.

01:02:18.726 --> 01:02:19.225
All right.

01:02:19.225 --> 01:02:19.790
Fine.

01:02:19.790 --> 01:02:22.122
Could you just distribute
the mic as you see people.

01:02:22.122 --> 01:02:23.330
I don't want to conduct this.

01:02:26.651 --> 01:02:27.150
Hi.

01:02:27.150 --> 01:02:29.010
My name is Robin.

01:02:29.010 --> 01:02:30.880
I wanted to thank
you for coming today.

01:02:30.880 --> 01:02:32.490
It's wonderful to hear you.

01:02:32.490 --> 01:02:36.240
And I wanted to just address
this woman's question what can

01:02:36.240 --> 01:02:36.880
we do.

01:02:36.880 --> 01:02:38.820
I think the first
thing-- everything--

01:02:38.820 --> 01:02:40.170
that was a great question.

01:02:40.170 --> 01:02:42.169
I always think of that myself.

01:02:42.169 --> 01:02:43.710
But I think the
first thing everybody

01:02:43.710 --> 01:02:48.300
has to do is vote, whether
it's here or in Israel.

01:02:48.300 --> 01:02:51.690
We've all got to vote and
make our legal representatives

01:02:51.690 --> 01:02:54.180
accountable for what
we think is right.

01:02:54.180 --> 01:02:58.920
But also I wanted to say that
we can support all the arts.

01:02:58.920 --> 01:03:02.010
We see Mohammed Assaf has
been out there creating

01:03:02.010 --> 01:03:04.350
a lot of national pride.

01:03:04.350 --> 01:03:06.210
We've had the recent
Palestinian film

01:03:06.210 --> 01:03:09.270
festival in Boston,
which was magnificent

01:03:09.270 --> 01:03:13.860
and very rich representation
of the arts Boston

01:03:13.860 --> 01:03:15.990
has a wonderful
Palestinian comedian

01:03:15.990 --> 01:03:19.890
who communicates
with humor, love,

01:03:19.890 --> 01:03:21.600
and tremendous national pride.

01:03:21.600 --> 01:03:22.440
Who's that?

01:03:22.440 --> 01:03:24.990
I can't think of
his name right now.

01:03:24.990 --> 01:03:26.530
Do you remember his name?

01:03:26.530 --> 01:03:27.880
I can't remember his name.

01:03:27.880 --> 01:03:30.120
And we have the center
of Arabic culture

01:03:30.120 --> 01:03:35.730
which often has social events
that celebrates and promotes

01:03:35.730 --> 01:03:36.770
understanding.

01:03:36.770 --> 01:03:42.660
And so I just wanted to say
participating and asking

01:03:42.660 --> 01:03:45.650
ourselves what can we
do is really important.

01:03:45.650 --> 01:03:47.220
And if you can't
remember his name,

01:03:47.220 --> 01:03:48.636
can you remember
one of his jokes?

01:03:51.839 --> 01:03:53.130
Not right now, I'm too nervous.

01:03:53.130 --> 01:03:56.124
[LAUGHTER]

01:03:58.119 --> 01:03:58.619
[INAUDIBLE]

01:03:58.619 --> 01:04:00.116
Gentleman in the green.

01:04:04.022 --> 01:04:05.980
We don't know what the
Trump plan is because he

01:04:05.980 --> 01:04:07.670
hasn't presented it yet.

01:04:07.670 --> 01:04:09.910
However, he did make
the startling statement

01:04:09.910 --> 01:04:12.100
that the negotiations will
be easier because he's

01:04:12.100 --> 01:04:14.140
taken Jerusalem off
the table, which

01:04:14.140 --> 01:04:16.420
is really incomprehensible.

01:04:16.420 --> 01:04:18.187
Rumors of the plan,
though, suggest

01:04:18.187 --> 01:04:20.020
that it's some kind of
a rump state with Abu

01:04:20.020 --> 01:04:22.691
Dis as its nominal capital.

01:04:22.691 --> 01:04:24.940
And Israel, of course,
continues to refer to Jerusalem

01:04:24.940 --> 01:04:26.600
as its undivided capital.

01:04:26.600 --> 01:04:28.990
So I'm wondering whether
this is really a red line,

01:04:28.990 --> 01:04:31.300
whether the protests in
Gaza or the beginnings

01:04:31.300 --> 01:04:34.750
of a fourth intifada and
whether New Jerusalem really

01:04:34.750 --> 01:04:39.280
is, just to be very
specific, non-negotiable.

01:04:39.280 --> 01:04:42.190
Jerusalem is
non-negotiable for us.

01:04:42.190 --> 01:04:46.510
We have to have
equal rights in it.

01:04:46.510 --> 01:04:48.168
It is non-negotiable.

01:04:48.168 --> 01:04:51.379
You're [? expecting ?]
[? a fourth ?] intifada is

01:04:51.379 --> 01:04:55.110
on its way [INAUDIBLE]?

01:04:55.110 --> 01:04:57.857
Gaza is under such pressure.

01:04:57.857 --> 01:05:00.315
Gaza is under such pressure,
people living in such poverty.

01:05:03.030 --> 01:05:08.280
They're living in such distress
that even if it explodes,

01:05:08.280 --> 01:05:10.470
it will simply implode.

01:05:10.470 --> 01:05:13.180
And this is what's
happening with it.

01:05:13.180 --> 01:05:19.110
And Gaza has to be addressed
at the humanitarian level.

01:05:19.110 --> 01:05:24.090
And it needs
emergency assistance.

01:05:24.090 --> 01:05:29.700
It needs both Israel, as well
as the Palestinian authority

01:05:29.700 --> 01:05:34.320
to open up, to facilitate.

01:05:34.320 --> 01:05:36.790
[INAUDIBLE] Egypt [INAUDIBLE].

01:05:36.790 --> 01:05:42.600
Egypt-- but you know, the
immediate neighbors and parties

01:05:42.600 --> 01:05:45.000
that are responsible
are both Israel

01:05:45.000 --> 01:05:46.290
and the Palestinian authority.

01:05:46.290 --> 01:05:48.330
And the Palestinian
authority has

01:05:48.330 --> 01:05:52.560
to look after the
people in Gaza.

01:05:52.560 --> 01:05:56.280
And Israel has to enable
the [? EPA ?] to look

01:05:56.280 --> 01:05:59.400
after the people in Gaza.

01:05:59.400 --> 01:06:01.616
But no, I don't think
there's an intifada coming.

01:06:01.616 --> 01:06:03.240
Although there's a
weekly, as you know,

01:06:03.240 --> 01:06:06.690
there's a weekly
march, every Friday.

01:06:06.690 --> 01:06:12.270
Yesterday, three kids 12
years old were killed.

01:06:15.361 --> 01:06:16.860
Apparently, they
thought they were--

01:06:16.860 --> 01:06:21.960
but I mean, they were putting
out things for catching birds,

01:06:21.960 --> 01:06:24.710
like 12-year-olds do.

01:06:24.710 --> 01:06:27.540
It's a distressful
situation in Gaza.

01:06:32.475 --> 01:06:37.400
[INAUDIBLE] a primary
barrier to the resolution

01:06:37.400 --> 01:06:40.960
of the Israeli-Palestinian
conflict,

01:06:40.960 --> 01:06:45.660
with the internal conflicts
among Israelis on the one hand

01:06:45.660 --> 01:06:47.950
and among Palestinians
on the other, which

01:06:47.950 --> 01:06:54.730
make the leadership challenges
extremely difficult. What hope

01:06:54.730 --> 01:06:58.280
do you see for
progress with respect

01:06:58.280 --> 01:07:01.790
to the internal conflicts
among Palestinians?

01:07:01.790 --> 01:07:05.300
Because some wonder whether
there's going to be one or two

01:07:05.300 --> 01:07:07.100
Palestinian states.

01:07:07.100 --> 01:07:09.920
I mean, given the
rather profound division

01:07:09.920 --> 01:07:15.970
that has at times led to almost
a civil war among Palestinians.

01:07:15.970 --> 01:07:20.930
With still more to come,
probably, in the near future--

01:07:20.930 --> 01:07:22.120
we didn't go into that.

01:07:22.120 --> 01:07:26.800
But yes, I mean,
we, as Palestinians,

01:07:26.800 --> 01:07:32.700
have a major crisis at the
moment in our leadership

01:07:32.700 --> 01:07:36.240
as a result of failure in the
peace process on the one hand

01:07:36.240 --> 01:07:42.530
and internal failures
on the other hand,

01:07:42.530 --> 01:07:47.250
in addition to the major
differences between Hamas

01:07:47.250 --> 01:07:49.240
and [INAUDIBLE] and so on.

01:07:49.240 --> 01:07:51.490
So we have a major problem.

01:07:51.490 --> 01:07:53.140
And we have to deal with it.

01:07:55.832 --> 01:07:58.780
And the Israelis,
of course, do, too.

01:07:58.780 --> 01:08:01.670
The Israelis have
a problem, I think.

01:08:01.670 --> 01:08:02.170
Yeah.

01:08:02.170 --> 01:08:06.520
I mean, yeah.

01:08:06.520 --> 01:08:10.168
But so what's the question?

01:08:10.168 --> 01:08:11.740
Well, the question is--

01:08:11.740 --> 01:08:12.780
What?

01:08:12.780 --> 01:08:14.075
For what?

01:08:14.075 --> 01:08:15.950
[LAUGHTER]

01:08:15.950 --> 01:08:16.450
42.

01:08:22.461 --> 01:08:22.960
Hi.

01:08:22.960 --> 01:08:26.474
My name is Talal [? Jabari. ?]
I'm a Palestinian diaspora.

01:08:26.474 --> 01:08:29.830
I study at HKS.

01:08:29.830 --> 01:08:31.740
I thought it was
really interesting,

01:08:31.740 --> 01:08:34.450
the example that you brought
up about the orchestra

01:08:34.450 --> 01:08:37.569
and about forging
a new identity.

01:08:37.569 --> 01:08:41.500
And obviously, being a
Palestinian diaspora,

01:08:41.500 --> 01:08:43.029
as I'm sure it is
for Palestinians

01:08:43.029 --> 01:08:46.130
who live in the
Palestinian territories,

01:08:46.130 --> 01:08:49.319
it's such a central
theme in our life.

01:08:49.319 --> 01:08:51.279
And so I was
wondering, you know,

01:08:51.279 --> 01:08:54.319
in forging that new identity,
what that would look like?

01:08:54.319 --> 01:08:56.800
And if you could
elaborate on that.

01:08:56.800 --> 01:08:59.790
And thank you for coming.

01:08:59.790 --> 01:09:02.000
Well, thank you for coming.

01:09:02.000 --> 01:09:04.040
But how come you're a
diaspora person if you're

01:09:04.040 --> 01:09:07.719
a [? Jabari. ?] I
don't understand.

01:09:07.719 --> 01:09:08.471
So--

01:09:08.471 --> 01:09:08.970
Yes.

01:09:08.970 --> 01:09:10.859
Go ahead.

01:09:10.859 --> 01:09:12.720
So my dad is actually Syrian.

01:09:12.720 --> 01:09:13.990
My mom's Palestinian.

01:09:13.990 --> 01:09:18.770
But I first and foremost
identify as Palestinian.

01:09:18.770 --> 01:09:20.180
That's a different story.

01:09:20.180 --> 01:09:20.680
OK.

01:09:25.210 --> 01:09:27.460
Well, I think that
[INAUDIBLE] will tell us

01:09:27.460 --> 01:09:31.040
about identities and forging
identities better than I can.

01:09:31.040 --> 01:09:32.620
But--

01:09:32.620 --> 01:09:33.687
Not tonight

01:09:33.687 --> 01:09:39.760
[LAUGHTER]

01:09:39.760 --> 01:09:43.640
But I think you can start with--

01:09:43.640 --> 01:09:48.350
it's hard when you-- it's
easier when you're talking,

01:09:48.350 --> 01:09:50.670
say, to a friend.

01:09:50.670 --> 01:09:54.620
And you can forge a kind
of identity between the two

01:09:54.620 --> 01:09:55.520
of you.

01:09:55.520 --> 01:09:58.280
And you can be anything,
and they can be anything.

01:09:58.280 --> 01:10:02.240
And the bigger the circle--

01:10:02.240 --> 01:10:05.270
again, this is reverting
to another wisdom,

01:10:05.270 --> 01:10:08.210
piece of wisdom my wife was
telling us this morning--

01:10:08.210 --> 01:10:13.400
the larger the circle, the
larger the circle of identity,

01:10:13.400 --> 01:10:17.210
the more difficult
it is to merge.

01:10:17.210 --> 01:10:20.780
So you have to start
small and work upwards.

01:10:20.780 --> 01:10:24.200
And I think if you form
a group, a small group,

01:10:24.200 --> 01:10:26.900
it can influence.

01:10:26.900 --> 01:10:29.750
It can have ripple
effects, perhaps.

01:10:29.750 --> 01:10:32.310
But then, as Robin
was saying earlier,

01:10:32.310 --> 01:10:35.930
I think at the end you have
to be effective politically

01:10:35.930 --> 01:10:39.710
by actually becoming a
politician, at least by voting.

01:10:39.710 --> 01:10:41.600
I mean you have to vote.

01:10:41.600 --> 01:10:44.640
But you can do far
more than voting,

01:10:44.640 --> 01:10:49.610
You can be more
active in creating

01:10:49.610 --> 01:10:51.160
this kind of community.

01:10:51.160 --> 01:10:53.780
There are many communities,
Israeli-Palestinian communities

01:10:53.780 --> 01:10:58.400
by the way that, I mean,
examples that we have

01:10:58.400 --> 01:11:01.310
that can be built upon.

01:11:01.310 --> 01:11:05.510
By the way, Robin, who spoke
before you is married to--

01:11:05.510 --> 01:11:09.800
I just discovered-- someone who
is a cousin, a distant cousin.

01:11:09.800 --> 01:11:13.328
He's a distant cousin who
was born in Syria, too.

01:11:13.328 --> 01:11:16.260
[INAUDIBLE]

01:11:16.260 --> 01:11:19.040
There you are.

01:11:19.040 --> 01:11:20.400
Yeah.

01:11:20.400 --> 01:11:23.990
Can I ask [? Lucy ?]
Nusseibeh to speak?

01:11:23.990 --> 01:11:29.510
Because clearly, you
have been inspiring Sari

01:11:29.510 --> 01:11:32.170
with these various
ideas all day.

01:11:32.170 --> 01:11:33.170
[LAUGHTER]

01:11:33.170 --> 01:11:36.290
Photographs in the
morning, circles

01:11:36.290 --> 01:11:39.380
of identification in the
afternoon-- so could you--

01:11:39.380 --> 01:11:42.620
and have your own NGO.

01:11:42.620 --> 01:11:45.710
And could you add
to this discussion

01:11:45.710 --> 01:11:50.060
by answering the good Leninist
question, what is to be done?

01:11:50.060 --> 01:11:51.830
[LAUGHTER]

01:11:51.830 --> 01:11:55.110
Take a step back.

01:11:55.110 --> 01:11:57.690
I don't think I could
answer the question at all.

01:11:57.690 --> 01:11:59.090
Thank you very much for the--

01:11:59.090 --> 01:12:00.250
What should not be done?

01:12:00.250 --> 01:12:02.300
--invitation.

01:12:02.300 --> 01:12:06.950
I mean, I think I would
just add to what others

01:12:06.950 --> 01:12:10.610
have been saying, the importance
of really reaching across

01:12:10.610 --> 01:12:14.060
to the humanity of other people.

01:12:14.060 --> 01:12:17.270
That part of what
seems to be going on

01:12:17.270 --> 01:12:21.890
is this aim,
polarizing, at allowing

01:12:21.890 --> 01:12:24.530
us to dehumanize other people.

01:12:24.530 --> 01:12:27.320
And that it's important
to resist this.

01:12:27.320 --> 01:12:31.040
And it's important to
resist the kind of despair

01:12:31.040 --> 01:12:34.360
and discouragement
that is thrown at us.

01:12:34.360 --> 01:12:40.850
The kind of resilience that Sari
actually exemplifies and was

01:12:40.850 --> 01:12:44.870
insisting on, I
think, earlier, this

01:12:44.870 --> 01:12:48.640
is really incredibly important.

01:12:48.640 --> 01:12:51.420
Not just in the
Israeli-Palestinian context,

01:12:51.420 --> 01:12:55.170
I think, but in a
more global context.

01:12:55.170 --> 01:13:00.360
As we look around us, we
have to reach out and say no!

01:13:00.360 --> 01:13:02.400
This is not who we are.

01:13:02.400 --> 01:13:06.530
And this is not how we will
accept seeing other people.

01:13:06.530 --> 01:13:11.380
We are insisting on
engaging with others

01:13:11.380 --> 01:13:17.950
as equal human beings with total
reciprocal respect, something

01:13:17.950 --> 01:13:18.890
like [INAUDIBLE].

01:13:18.890 --> 01:13:23.050
Lucy, can I ask you
whether these ideas

01:13:23.050 --> 01:13:26.050
of some kind of convergence
that you were talking

01:13:26.050 --> 01:13:28.600
about happened at
different levels,

01:13:28.600 --> 01:13:30.460
are there any in Jerusalem?

01:13:30.460 --> 01:13:32.860
Are there any
state institutions,

01:13:32.860 --> 01:13:35.290
or are there
national institutions

01:13:35.290 --> 01:13:36.340
that give you hope?

01:13:36.340 --> 01:13:40.000
For instance, in India, we
do have the Supreme Court.

01:13:40.000 --> 01:13:43.120
And give or take, we have
hope in the Supreme Court

01:13:43.120 --> 01:13:48.160
that minorities, social
justice issues will be,

01:13:48.160 --> 01:13:54.220
not always, but quite often
welcomed and hospitably dealt

01:13:54.220 --> 01:13:55.000
with.

01:13:55.000 --> 01:13:57.970
Are there any institutions in--

01:13:57.970 --> 01:13:59.050
for both of you--

01:13:59.050 --> 01:14:04.510
in the Israel-Palestinian
confluence

01:14:04.510 --> 01:14:08.500
that give you hope for the
future or for the present?

01:14:12.350 --> 01:14:13.520
I think there used to be.

01:14:13.520 --> 01:14:16.580
I can't think of
any at the moment.

01:14:16.580 --> 01:14:19.120
There is an interesting
case recently of--

01:14:19.120 --> 01:14:20.130
[INAUDIBLE]?

01:14:20.130 --> 01:14:20.980
No, no, no.

01:14:20.980 --> 01:14:23.960
But I was going to say there
is an interesting case of the--

01:14:23.960 --> 01:14:26.300
because you know, you would
say the Supreme Court,

01:14:26.300 --> 01:14:27.270
for instance.

01:14:27.270 --> 01:14:29.690
But in Israel, in
particular, that

01:14:29.690 --> 01:14:32.580
has been influenced by politics.

01:14:32.580 --> 01:14:35.420
And so it's not as
reliable as it was.

01:14:35.420 --> 01:14:38.510
But most recently,
for instance, there

01:14:38.510 --> 01:14:42.860
was this case of the
American Palestinian student

01:14:42.860 --> 01:14:46.580
who was coming in to study
at the Hebrew University.

01:14:46.580 --> 01:14:50.000
And she was prevented from
doing so to begin with.

01:14:50.000 --> 01:14:56.120
And actually, one of the things
that made her case stronger,

01:14:56.120 --> 01:14:58.580
that eventually
made a difference,

01:14:58.580 --> 01:15:01.850
was the fact that the
Hebrew University itself

01:15:01.850 --> 01:15:05.180
and the academics there, or
a sufficient number of them,

01:15:05.180 --> 01:15:08.400
stood up for her and
made a whole thing.

01:15:08.400 --> 01:15:11.300
And so finally, she is now at
the Hebrew University studying.

01:15:14.200 --> 01:15:15.320
[? Roger ?] [INAUDIBLE].

01:15:15.320 --> 01:15:16.030
Speak without the mic?

01:15:16.030 --> 01:15:16.530
Yeah.

01:15:16.530 --> 01:15:18.900
We don't need mics here.

01:15:18.900 --> 01:15:24.790
The case you've just raised
is very interesting to me

01:15:24.790 --> 01:15:25.290
personally.

01:15:25.290 --> 01:15:31.230
Because that young woman
was interested in pursuing

01:15:31.230 --> 01:15:36.675
the study of international human
rights at Hebrew University,

01:15:36.675 --> 01:15:41.150
which makes the denial of her
entry all the more poignant.

01:15:41.150 --> 01:15:43.951
But as I understand
it, one of the facts

01:15:43.951 --> 01:15:48.861
that counted in her favor is
that although at an earlier

01:15:48.861 --> 01:15:52.298
point in her studies as
a student [INAUDIBLE],,

01:15:52.298 --> 01:15:55.735
she had been a proponent of the
boycott [INAUDIBLE] sanction

01:15:55.735 --> 01:16:01.136
that she had later
renounced that stance

01:16:01.136 --> 01:16:04.475
and that this
counted in her favor.

01:16:04.475 --> 01:16:06.850
I'm perhaps putting
you on the spot.

01:16:06.850 --> 01:16:10.238
Could-- at least
among diapora Jews

01:16:10.238 --> 01:16:14.174
who oppose current
Israeli policy,

01:16:14.174 --> 01:16:17.864
the BDS movement is
usually seen as one

01:16:17.864 --> 01:16:23.522
of the most divisive factors.

01:16:23.522 --> 01:16:27.950
Friends of mine, like
[INAUDIBLE],, no relation,

01:16:27.950 --> 01:16:33.035
apparently, who supported are
ostracized by certain portions

01:16:33.035 --> 01:16:35.240
of the Jewish community.

01:16:35.240 --> 01:16:37.690
And her case, in particular,
was very interesting,

01:16:37.690 --> 01:16:40.140
[INAUDIBLE] where her
renunciation of that tactic

01:16:40.140 --> 01:16:43.090
seems to have played a
role in her admission.

01:16:43.090 --> 01:16:46.167
And I'm curious,
from your perspective

01:16:46.167 --> 01:16:51.354
on the Palestinian
side, whether BDS

01:16:51.354 --> 01:16:57.776
seems to have any
constructive role to play

01:16:57.776 --> 01:17:07.180
or whether it's seen as largely
irrelevant to [INAUDIBLE]..

01:17:07.180 --> 01:17:11.860
So this is putting me
on this on the spot.

01:17:11.860 --> 01:17:14.750
It's a very difficult question.

01:17:14.750 --> 01:17:19.580
Look, let me start
somewhere else on BDS.

01:17:19.580 --> 01:17:23.890
Because normally, when people
talk, the Palestinians talk

01:17:23.890 --> 01:17:27.280
about BDS, they not
only are thinking

01:17:27.280 --> 01:17:29.860
of Americans or Europeans.

01:17:29.860 --> 01:17:31.960
They're thinking
of Palestinians.

01:17:31.960 --> 01:17:37.090
And they're saying basically
that, in Palestine itself,

01:17:37.090 --> 01:17:40.675
we, the Palestinians,
should boycott

01:17:40.675 --> 01:17:43.240
our counterparts, Israelis.

01:17:43.240 --> 01:17:44.360
So what does that mean?

01:17:44.360 --> 01:17:47.020
It means basically
boycotting everything--

01:17:47.020 --> 01:17:50.972
from the economic to the
trade to the commerce to this,

01:17:50.972 --> 01:17:51.760
to this--

01:17:51.760 --> 01:17:53.320
right up to the
negotiation level.

01:17:58.100 --> 01:18:00.940
This is something
that is, I think,

01:18:00.940 --> 01:18:04.450
a thing entirely
separate from the call

01:18:04.450 --> 01:18:09.700
for Europeans or Americans
to boycott Israel, right?

01:18:09.700 --> 01:18:12.520
And you know, I would argue
very strongly, personally,

01:18:12.520 --> 01:18:15.820
that the level of the
Palestinians, the thrust,

01:18:15.820 --> 01:18:20.380
the force shouldn't be
to boycott, but to do

01:18:20.380 --> 01:18:24.640
the opposite, to engage.

01:18:24.640 --> 01:18:27.430
Because that is the way
to bring the Israelis

01:18:27.430 --> 01:18:31.340
and the Palestinians
closer to one another.

01:18:31.340 --> 01:18:37.240
Now concerning the outside,
now, I think it varies.

01:18:37.240 --> 01:18:40.660
As far as the Jewish
community is concerned,

01:18:40.660 --> 01:18:45.820
I think this is a situation
that has to be solved

01:18:45.820 --> 01:18:47.570
within the Jewish community.

01:18:47.570 --> 01:18:52.060
But I'll tell you as far as
the non-Jewish community is

01:18:52.060 --> 01:18:53.140
concerned.

01:18:53.140 --> 01:18:57.310
Because in the past,
I've had situations

01:18:57.310 --> 01:19:03.400
where more than once someone
was invited to Israel

01:19:03.400 --> 01:19:06.310
to participate in a talk at
the Hebrew University or Tel

01:19:06.310 --> 01:19:07.750
Aviv or somewhere--

01:19:07.750 --> 01:19:10.060
would write to me and say,
look, I've been invited.

01:19:10.060 --> 01:19:11.350
I'm worried about this BDS.

01:19:11.350 --> 01:19:12.550
What do you think?

01:19:12.550 --> 01:19:18.010
And can I come and give a
talk at your university,

01:19:18.010 --> 01:19:20.660
somehow, to sort
of balance this.

01:19:20.660 --> 01:19:27.260
And my reaction
would have been, was,

01:19:27.260 --> 01:19:29.680
in fact, on more
than one occasion,

01:19:29.680 --> 01:19:32.560
that they should make
up their own minds what

01:19:32.560 --> 01:19:34.430
they wanted to do.

01:19:34.430 --> 01:19:39.340
But in any case, if they
decided to come and participate

01:19:39.340 --> 01:19:45.130
in whatever, then they would
be welcome to come and give

01:19:45.130 --> 01:19:49.480
a talk at our place,
but not to use the fact

01:19:49.480 --> 01:19:52.480
that they are coming to give
a talk at our university

01:19:52.480 --> 01:19:57.760
as a kind of justification
to go and talk over there.

01:19:57.760 --> 01:20:02.020
But they have to go through
the ethical, if you like,

01:20:02.020 --> 01:20:04.180
management processing
themselves.

01:20:04.180 --> 01:20:11.420
They have to decide what best
fits their moral bearings.

01:20:11.420 --> 01:20:13.330
Now has it been useful?

01:20:13.330 --> 01:20:18.070
In many ways, the campaign
for BDS in American campuses,

01:20:18.070 --> 01:20:22.270
in Europe, has been useful in
the sense it's raised awareness

01:20:22.270 --> 01:20:27.490
in a way that this did not
happen before concerning

01:20:27.490 --> 01:20:28.480
the Palestinian plight.

01:20:28.480 --> 01:20:33.560
So there is that part of it
which you can say is positive.

01:20:33.560 --> 01:20:38.110
On the other hand, it's
also created more friction,

01:20:38.110 --> 01:20:41.860
whether within the Jewish
community or between the pros--

01:20:41.860 --> 01:20:44.650
you know, the pro-Israel and
the pro-Palestinian groups.

01:20:44.650 --> 01:20:48.190
And you see, if you're
thinking like me,

01:20:48.190 --> 01:20:50.800
then you're thinking
you want to make--

01:20:50.800 --> 01:20:52.370
this is a point I made earlier--

01:20:52.370 --> 01:20:55.720
you want to make the pro-Israels
and the pro-Palestinians

01:20:55.720 --> 01:20:57.820
actually to make peace
between one another.

01:20:57.820 --> 01:20:59.530
That's what you want to do.

01:20:59.530 --> 01:21:01.660
And you don't want to
create the friction.

01:21:01.660 --> 01:21:04.390
And you need that
peace abroad in order

01:21:04.390 --> 01:21:07.090
to support the peace within.

01:21:07.090 --> 01:21:09.430
So how do you solve this puzzle?

01:21:12.610 --> 01:21:14.380
You should go to
the United Nations

01:21:14.380 --> 01:21:20.470
and ask for
intervention and to get

01:21:20.470 --> 01:21:22.150
pro-Israelis and
pro-Palestinians

01:21:22.150 --> 01:21:26.170
to get together.

01:21:26.170 --> 01:21:33.440
Because the conflict
outside actually only

01:21:33.440 --> 01:21:35.930
serves to create
more conflict inside.

01:21:42.281 --> 01:21:42.780
Thanks.

01:21:42.780 --> 01:21:45.600
Talking about boycotts
and academic boycotts

01:21:45.600 --> 01:21:49.740
that you mentioned, as a
former president of Al-Quds

01:21:49.740 --> 01:21:52.710
University, how do
you see the boycott?

01:21:52.710 --> 01:21:55.212
If I understood well,
Palestinian universities

01:21:55.212 --> 01:21:56.670
boycott [INAUDIBLE]
are not allowed

01:21:56.670 --> 01:21:58.980
to collaborate with
Israeli universities.

01:21:58.980 --> 01:22:00.660
So how do you see this?

01:22:00.660 --> 01:22:04.450
Would you favor collaborations
of Palestinian universities?

01:22:04.450 --> 01:22:04.980
I do.

01:22:04.980 --> 01:22:07.470
I do is the simple answer.

01:22:07.470 --> 01:22:09.960
I mean, I do, in fact.

01:22:09.960 --> 01:22:15.990
But my position has been
very unpopular in the past.

01:22:15.990 --> 01:22:19.800
[INAUDIBLE] At first, as you
say, the Council for Education,

01:22:19.800 --> 01:22:23.250
the Palestinian Council for
Education, took a position--

01:22:23.250 --> 01:22:24.690
this is even after Oslo--

01:22:27.510 --> 01:22:31.200
to not to have any, to
prevent any connections

01:22:31.200 --> 01:22:33.480
between Israeli and
Palestinian universities.

01:22:33.480 --> 01:22:37.650
I was a member of the
Council for Education.

01:22:37.650 --> 01:22:41.280
And I said to the
Council that I will not

01:22:41.280 --> 01:22:42.670
abide by this decision.

01:22:42.670 --> 01:22:44.880
And we are an
independent institution.

01:22:44.880 --> 01:22:46.170
You want to go this way, fine.

01:22:46.170 --> 01:22:48.750
But you know, my
way is different.

01:22:48.750 --> 01:22:54.210
And we, in fact, did go
on and institute relations

01:22:54.210 --> 01:22:57.480
with Israeli counterparts
all the way up to 2000--

01:22:57.480 --> 01:23:00.240
I think, and 14,
was it-- or whenever

01:23:00.240 --> 01:23:04.290
it was that Israel invaded
Gaza the second time.

01:23:04.290 --> 01:23:06.120
And [INAUDIBLE] the first time.

01:23:06.120 --> 01:23:09.180
And at that point,
it became very hard.

01:23:09.180 --> 01:23:14.400
And I convened a meeting with
all the Palestinian academics

01:23:14.400 --> 01:23:16.980
at my university who
were engaged in projects

01:23:16.980 --> 01:23:18.760
with Israeli counterparts.

01:23:18.760 --> 01:23:20.790
And I asked them how
they felt, and it

01:23:20.790 --> 01:23:25.990
was a very emotional point,
emotional period at that time.

01:23:25.990 --> 01:23:30.210
And after a lot of discussion,
the majority decision was,

01:23:30.210 --> 01:23:33.030
you know, should
suspend our relations

01:23:33.030 --> 01:23:34.980
with Israeli counterparts.

01:23:34.980 --> 01:23:40.600
But we should look again at
this after a period of time.

01:23:40.600 --> 01:23:43.810
But we should not stop anything
that's ongoing at the moment.

01:23:43.810 --> 01:23:45.050
So there was that.

01:23:45.050 --> 01:23:47.119
And after I left
the administration,

01:23:47.119 --> 01:23:48.660
I think people at
the University have

01:23:48.660 --> 01:23:51.870
been less enthusiastic about.

01:23:51.870 --> 01:23:54.990
But as I was saying
earlier, I mean,

01:23:54.990 --> 01:24:00.370
in the case of the
Israeli-Palestinian relations,

01:24:00.370 --> 01:24:03.520
you know there are many
things you can boycott.

01:24:03.520 --> 01:24:07.710
And I think the last
one you want to boycott

01:24:07.710 --> 01:24:10.200
is, in fact,
academic cooperation.

01:24:10.200 --> 01:24:14.430
I mean you can start with
the mafia on both sides.

01:24:14.430 --> 01:24:17.430
And stop them from cooperating.

01:24:17.430 --> 01:24:20.250
And the underworld, there's
a lot of cooperation.

01:24:20.250 --> 01:24:21.840
And you know, and you can go--

01:24:21.840 --> 01:24:22.511
Adelson.

01:24:22.511 --> 01:24:23.010
Adelson.

01:24:23.010 --> 01:24:23.775
Adelson, yeah.

01:24:23.775 --> 01:24:24.990
[LAUGHS]

01:24:24.990 --> 01:24:26.820
Academics, I think,
should be able to--

01:24:26.820 --> 01:24:30.360
and actually, we stand to
benefit, the Palestinians,

01:24:30.360 --> 01:24:32.010
from this cooperation.

01:24:32.010 --> 01:24:32.700
Please.

01:24:32.700 --> 01:24:32.930
Sorry.

01:24:32.930 --> 01:24:34.429
You've been waiting
for a long time.

01:24:34.429 --> 01:24:35.080
I apologize.

01:24:35.080 --> 01:24:36.060
Thank you.

01:24:36.060 --> 01:24:40.530
I have a question about the
whole concept of sharing.

01:24:40.530 --> 01:24:46.950
And I wonder how it
works when one side comes

01:24:46.950 --> 01:24:52.650
to the table holding all of
the cards or all of the oranges

01:24:52.650 --> 01:24:59.160
or all of the cakes, and the
other side doesn't have it.

01:24:59.160 --> 01:25:04.010
So does the concept
of sharing work there,

01:25:04.010 --> 01:25:10.860
or is it more a matter
of giving and receiving?

01:25:10.860 --> 01:25:16.830
And if the latter, then to what
extent does the giver really

01:25:16.830 --> 01:25:18.510
want to give?

01:25:18.510 --> 01:25:21.960
And to what extent does
the recipient really

01:25:21.960 --> 01:25:24.430
want to receive?

01:25:24.430 --> 01:25:30.820
So I have a little bit of doubt
about this notion of sharing,

01:25:30.820 --> 01:25:33.810
although I believe
in it firmly myself.

01:25:33.810 --> 01:25:35.780
Well, as [INAUDIBLE]
was saying earlier,

01:25:35.780 --> 01:25:37.360
I think one of the
things you have

01:25:37.360 --> 01:25:40.420
to do when you come
to the table is

01:25:40.420 --> 01:25:45.760
to change who you are
sitting in front of.

01:25:45.760 --> 01:25:51.310
So of course, I mean, I think
there's [INAUDIBLE] point

01:25:51.310 --> 01:25:57.460
that, of course, a negotiator
or the party that is negotiating

01:25:57.460 --> 01:26:04.120
with you has to be somehow
worked in order to begin

01:26:04.120 --> 01:26:06.020
to see you differently.

01:26:06.020 --> 01:26:10.480
And I think once they do
that, then it's not a matter--

01:26:10.480 --> 01:26:14.650
it ceases to be a matter
of giving as a kind of-- it

01:26:14.650 --> 01:26:18.820
becomes a matter of,
perhaps, a moral imperative,

01:26:18.820 --> 01:26:21.490
or perhaps even a need.

01:26:21.490 --> 01:26:23.980
In the case of the Israelis
and the Palestinians,

01:26:23.980 --> 01:26:27.010
I'll tell you something that
struck me some time ago, when

01:26:27.010 --> 01:26:28.330
I was younger.

01:26:28.330 --> 01:26:31.430
That Shimon Peres said--

01:26:31.430 --> 01:26:35.650
that I used very often--

01:26:35.650 --> 01:26:40.060
at one stage, Shimon Peres
was actually trying to get--

01:26:40.060 --> 01:26:42.370
he was talking about
the need to make peace

01:26:42.370 --> 01:26:43.570
with the Palestinians.

01:26:43.570 --> 01:26:45.100
This was in the '80s.

01:26:45.100 --> 01:26:46.090
It was in the mid-'80s.

01:26:46.090 --> 01:26:48.080
So it was before anything.

01:26:48.080 --> 01:26:51.610
And he was making this
statement to Israelis

01:26:51.610 --> 01:26:54.250
in his own backyard,
so to speak.

01:26:54.250 --> 01:26:57.480
And he said something like this.

01:26:57.480 --> 01:27:00.840
He was telling them, we
have to make an exchange

01:27:00.840 --> 01:27:01.800
with the Palestinians.

01:27:01.800 --> 01:27:07.590
Because it is true that we,
the Israelis, hold the present.

01:27:07.590 --> 01:27:10.380
But the Palestinians
hold the future.

01:27:10.380 --> 01:27:12.780
And the exchange
you have to make

01:27:12.780 --> 01:27:15.570
is for us to give them
a part of the presence

01:27:15.570 --> 01:27:19.290
so that they can give
us a part of the future.

01:27:19.290 --> 01:27:21.060
This is the real exchange.

01:27:21.060 --> 01:27:23.430
And so we the Palestinians
actually are not

01:27:23.430 --> 01:27:25.650
weak at the negotiating table.

01:27:25.650 --> 01:27:29.100
Yes, we don't have guns, or
we don't have enough of them.

01:27:29.100 --> 01:27:30.030
We don't have rockets.

01:27:30.030 --> 01:27:31.590
We don't have all of that.

01:27:31.590 --> 01:27:34.260
But don't be mistaken.

01:27:34.260 --> 01:27:35.940
We are very strong.

01:27:35.940 --> 01:27:38.076
We are very strong.

01:27:38.076 --> 01:27:40.700
So there is a question here, and
then there's a question there.

01:27:40.700 --> 01:27:41.510
You want a question.

01:27:41.510 --> 01:27:42.551
That's the last question.

01:27:42.551 --> 01:27:43.700
So one, two, yeah.

01:27:43.700 --> 01:27:44.630
Thank you.

01:27:44.630 --> 01:27:46.080
Thank you so much.

01:27:46.080 --> 01:27:50.510
So the language and the rhetoric
of oranges and their sharing,

01:27:50.510 --> 01:27:52.970
as well as the
language of sharing

01:27:52.970 --> 01:27:55.670
in the title of the
conversation and the rhetoric,

01:27:55.670 --> 01:27:58.110
the attendant rhetoric
of giving and exchange,

01:27:58.110 --> 01:28:00.530
all that reminds me of
the kind of language

01:28:00.530 --> 01:28:02.270
that is used in a
considerable chunk

01:28:02.270 --> 01:28:05.720
of the academic literature
on Israel-Palestine.

01:28:05.720 --> 01:28:09.980
Which really uses the language
of settler colonialism

01:28:09.980 --> 01:28:11.930
as the basis, as
the primary basis

01:28:11.930 --> 01:28:14.720
for making sense of
what sharing is like.

01:28:14.720 --> 01:28:16.730
And I take the last
sentiment to be

01:28:16.730 --> 01:28:19.010
attendant to the ways in
which a straightforward

01:28:19.010 --> 01:28:21.920
metaphor of sharing
might not be as

01:28:21.920 --> 01:28:24.830
attendant to the
political imbalances that

01:28:24.830 --> 01:28:27.840
are historically
mediated and sedimented.

01:28:27.840 --> 01:28:31.220
So my question is really
about in what ways

01:28:31.220 --> 01:28:33.800
can we have the
historical process

01:28:33.800 --> 01:28:36.170
and the ongoing, indeed,
historical process of settler

01:28:36.170 --> 01:28:39.350
colonialism be central to
a conversation about going

01:28:39.350 --> 01:28:40.860
forward?

01:28:40.860 --> 01:28:43.490
And one way in which I've
been struggling with this is

01:28:43.490 --> 01:28:45.470
is precisely through
the coalitions

01:28:45.470 --> 01:28:49.490
that have been forming recently
between Jews and Palestinians

01:28:49.490 --> 01:28:52.460
and indeed, non-Jews
and non-Palestinians

01:28:52.460 --> 01:28:55.220
around a settler colonial
perspective that recognizes

01:28:55.220 --> 01:28:58.760
the extent, ways in which
religion and culture play

01:28:58.760 --> 01:29:01.310
a role, but also points
to their contingency.

01:29:01.310 --> 01:29:03.840
And so you can have
an anti-Zionist Jew,

01:29:03.840 --> 01:29:07.220
and an anti-Zionist Palestinian,
and an anti-Zionist humanist

01:29:07.220 --> 01:29:10.610
working together
for a way of life,

01:29:10.610 --> 01:29:14.180
a cohabitation that recognizes
the humanity of everyone

01:29:14.180 --> 01:29:16.610
there in ways,
perhaps, that fall

01:29:16.610 --> 01:29:19.106
beyond the rhetoric of sharing.

01:29:19.106 --> 01:29:20.480
So I'm wondering
if you can speak

01:29:20.480 --> 01:29:22.820
to the question of
language and the framework

01:29:22.820 --> 01:29:26.660
that we've been using in
making sense of the issue.

01:29:26.660 --> 01:29:30.250
Well, I mean, don't
forget when we

01:29:30.250 --> 01:29:33.610
use the term sharing
in this context,

01:29:33.610 --> 01:29:37.000
we're thinking in
terms of the existing

01:29:37.000 --> 01:29:40.270
parameters, political
parameters which

01:29:40.270 --> 01:29:46.030
are to do with having to
try and still make out

01:29:46.030 --> 01:29:50.440
a case for some kind of
resolution between the Israelis

01:29:50.440 --> 01:29:53.650
and the Palestinians on the
basis of two states, basically.

01:29:53.650 --> 01:29:54.430
All right?

01:29:54.430 --> 01:29:56.800
And you know, if
you cannot do that,

01:29:56.800 --> 01:30:01.030
we're still thinking in the
context of the same parameters.

01:30:01.030 --> 01:30:05.890
We're thinking if that's
not possible, then

01:30:05.890 --> 01:30:10.030
how else within, again, the
existing circumstances can

01:30:10.030 --> 01:30:16.360
we, in any case, bring about
some kind of an equitable

01:30:16.360 --> 01:30:22.510
kind of living condition for
both Israelis and Palestinians.

01:30:22.510 --> 01:30:28.430
Now what you're saying, in
fact, pushes a bit further.

01:30:28.430 --> 01:30:31.870
What you're doing is
basically telling us

01:30:31.870 --> 01:30:35.170
we should reconsider
the parameters.

01:30:35.170 --> 01:30:37.420
And you know, the
parameters that

01:30:37.420 --> 01:30:41.020
are being used in
the modern context

01:30:41.020 --> 01:30:44.740
or in the existing context
do not actually work.

01:30:44.740 --> 01:30:46.210
And you may be right.

01:30:46.210 --> 01:30:48.820
And actually, it's
something that is--

01:30:48.820 --> 01:30:51.670
I mean, I mentioned it
earlier-- that it's something

01:30:51.670 --> 01:30:53.170
that does occur to one.

01:30:53.170 --> 01:30:56.980
That maybe, for instance,
Zionism as such,

01:30:56.980 --> 01:31:03.390
even Palestinian nationalism
as such are just as they are

01:31:03.390 --> 01:31:06.300
and as [? they ?] become
are things that cannot

01:31:06.300 --> 01:31:13.350
of themselves resolve into
something that as you call

01:31:13.350 --> 01:31:19.890
humanitarian humanitarian
state of peace between people.

01:31:19.890 --> 01:31:25.210
Well, I think we
have to work slowly.

01:31:25.210 --> 01:31:30.250
I mean, I'm prepared to
look at my case, at my age,

01:31:30.250 --> 01:31:36.130
I'm prepared to look at every
way people offer you to push

01:31:36.130 --> 01:31:46.370
forward and towards peace and on
a peace that will be equitable,

01:31:46.370 --> 01:31:49.430
that will offer
dignity and respect

01:31:49.430 --> 01:31:53.870
for different people,
different individuals belonging

01:31:53.870 --> 01:31:57.547
to different backgrounds.

01:31:57.547 --> 01:31:59.380
And at the end of the
day, it doesn't really

01:31:59.380 --> 01:32:07.930
matter very much how you get
there or what sort of theoretic

01:32:07.930 --> 01:32:10.150
construct you use in
order to get there.

01:32:10.150 --> 01:32:13.270
In my case, say, as a
person living in Jerusalem,

01:32:13.270 --> 01:32:17.110
all I need is to finally
find peace at home.

01:32:17.110 --> 01:32:20.005
Now you know whether through
this theoretic construct

01:32:20.005 --> 01:32:25.510
or that, at the end of the
day, it's secondary for me.

01:32:25.510 --> 01:32:26.410
But you're right.

01:32:26.410 --> 01:32:31.160
I mean, I think
the language we use

01:32:31.160 --> 01:32:36.860
is very much stuck to a
certain framework of politics

01:32:36.860 --> 01:32:43.240
that we are today following.

01:32:43.240 --> 01:32:45.810
A peace with dignity,
peace with equality--

01:32:45.810 --> 01:32:48.070
so that's where all
the rubs come in.

01:32:48.070 --> 01:32:54.490
If you're willing to accept some
kind of ad [? hocary, ?] then

01:32:54.490 --> 01:32:55.909
you can get a kind of peace.

01:32:55.909 --> 01:32:58.450
But it's not with dignity and
equality, which is your demand.

01:32:58.450 --> 01:32:59.961
Yes, a final question, please.

01:32:59.961 --> 01:33:00.460
Hi.

01:33:00.460 --> 01:33:01.760
Thank you so much for coming.

01:33:01.760 --> 01:33:07.070
My question is kind of going off
of what Abdullah's just said,

01:33:07.070 --> 01:33:09.550
We've talked so much about
understanding and reaching

01:33:09.550 --> 01:33:11.750
across for that understanding.

01:33:11.750 --> 01:33:15.760
But I haven't heard
the word responsibility

01:33:15.760 --> 01:33:17.770
or accountability
be used so much.

01:33:17.770 --> 01:33:20.620
And I feel like the
root of this is really

01:33:20.620 --> 01:33:23.050
within Israeli
society to overcome

01:33:23.050 --> 01:33:27.980
a great deal of denial of
accountability in the region.

01:33:27.980 --> 01:33:31.380
And we're talking a lot
about recognizing each other

01:33:31.380 --> 01:33:32.990
as human beings.

01:33:32.990 --> 01:33:36.730
And the Israeli military's
behavior on the Gaza Strip

01:33:36.730 --> 01:33:42.740
is not recognition of
Palestinians as human beings.

01:33:42.740 --> 01:33:48.250
And so I want to just to
end, if you have any--

01:33:48.250 --> 01:33:52.780
to my mind, the only
kind of route, at least,

01:33:52.780 --> 01:33:55.960
might be within local
communities in Israel

01:33:55.960 --> 01:33:57.760
to begin to have
these conversations,

01:33:57.760 --> 01:34:01.120
to begin to start even talking
about the idea of settler

01:34:01.120 --> 01:34:04.640
colonialism, which is
not discussed widespread

01:34:04.640 --> 01:34:06.850
in the Israeli youth.

01:34:06.850 --> 01:34:11.500
And one idea that's
applicable, perhaps,

01:34:11.500 --> 01:34:13.240
is the idea of truth
commissions, which

01:34:13.240 --> 01:34:17.260
has been used in South Africa.

01:34:17.260 --> 01:34:21.070
And I wonder if you know of
any, or involved with any,

01:34:21.070 --> 01:34:26.360
or promote any discussion
groups among the young people,

01:34:26.360 --> 01:34:31.400
among education groups in
Palestinian communities,

01:34:31.400 --> 01:34:33.770
or if you know of any
within Israeli communities

01:34:33.770 --> 01:34:37.220
that adopt these kind
of values of recognition

01:34:37.220 --> 01:34:40.040
that might overcome some of
this denial and blindness

01:34:40.040 --> 01:34:43.100
on the part of Israelis.

01:34:43.100 --> 01:34:46.500
Well, you know, your question
is very difficult to answer.

01:34:46.500 --> 01:34:49.500
I mean, I don't really
know such groups.

01:34:49.500 --> 01:34:56.290
I think that the problem
is-- is to have such groups.

01:34:56.290 --> 01:34:59.140
I mean, the problem is
that people, as you say,

01:34:59.140 --> 01:35:01.810
are in denial of
their responsibility.

01:35:05.330 --> 01:35:09.370
If you think about
Israel as the soldiers

01:35:09.370 --> 01:35:12.670
that are shooting at
the people in Gaza,

01:35:12.670 --> 01:35:20.160
or if you think of
Israel as the occupation,

01:35:20.160 --> 01:35:24.990
or Israel as the
colonial movement,

01:35:24.990 --> 01:35:30.840
or you know, as the displacement
movement of the Palestinians.

01:35:30.840 --> 01:35:34.260
And if on the Israeli side,
you think of the Palestinians

01:35:34.260 --> 01:35:36.000
as the terrorists,
and as I don't

01:35:36.000 --> 01:35:38.430
know what and what
and what, it's

01:35:38.430 --> 01:35:43.360
very hard to get
either side to think

01:35:43.360 --> 01:35:47.120
in terms of reconsidering
their self view,

01:35:47.120 --> 01:35:50.230
their self appreciation.

01:35:53.460 --> 01:35:56.220
And so it's sort of
going to take time

01:35:56.220 --> 01:35:59.850
to get there to the point
where you can start,

01:35:59.850 --> 01:36:04.800
for instance, like, commissions
that will look into,

01:36:04.800 --> 01:36:07.440
that will accept
responsibility on the part

01:36:07.440 --> 01:36:09.780
of the entire group.

01:36:09.780 --> 01:36:11.500
I think it'll take a long time.

01:36:11.500 --> 01:36:14.040
I don't know of any
that exists today.

01:36:14.040 --> 01:36:16.470
I mean, there are
Israeli groups,

01:36:16.470 --> 01:36:24.170
like, for instance, the soldiers
and so on who were wonderful

01:36:24.170 --> 01:36:24.980
stories.

01:36:24.980 --> 01:36:30.800
I mean, I was reading something
by David Schulman recently,

01:36:30.800 --> 01:36:33.590
who is at the H University.

01:36:33.590 --> 01:36:38.870
Something even more
interesting by a woman

01:36:38.870 --> 01:36:41.750
called Hillerman, I
think, Dr. Hillerman.

01:36:41.750 --> 01:36:44.390
She produced her book in
Hebrew about two years ago.

01:36:44.390 --> 01:36:49.040
But now it's coming
out in English--

01:36:49.040 --> 01:36:51.360
I think Chicago Press.

01:36:51.360 --> 01:36:58.440
And I mean, you read her, and
you see that she actually--

01:36:58.440 --> 01:37:02.580
I mean, she's accompanied
Palestinian workers.

01:37:02.580 --> 01:37:05.310
She's accompanied
Palestinian prisoners.

01:37:05.310 --> 01:37:06.990
She has gone to jail.

01:37:06.990 --> 01:37:10.020
She's been in the middle
of Gaza, the middle of--

01:37:10.020 --> 01:37:11.970
and in each and
every corner, she

01:37:11.970 --> 01:37:17.630
is describing exactly
how she sees--

01:37:17.630 --> 01:37:19.640
the underdog, the
Palestinians being treated,

01:37:19.640 --> 01:37:21.110
that kind of situation.

01:37:21.110 --> 01:37:25.580
And this kind of
testimony, I think,

01:37:25.580 --> 01:37:27.470
is something very important.

01:37:27.470 --> 01:37:31.550
Not only because it tells
about the Palestinians.

01:37:31.550 --> 01:37:36.510
I think because, as I see it,
it does also about herself.

01:37:36.510 --> 01:37:40.700
It tells about the existence of
this human spirit in the midst

01:37:40.700 --> 01:37:42.290
of the Israeli, you know.

01:37:42.290 --> 01:37:45.510
In this case living
in West Jerusalem.

01:37:45.510 --> 01:37:48.520
So you just have to
have more of this.

01:37:48.520 --> 01:37:52.760
You know, sometime, sometime
further on in the future,

01:37:52.760 --> 01:37:55.380
maybe you'll have a
commission of human rights.

01:37:55.380 --> 01:37:58.490
And we'll be able to.

01:37:58.490 --> 01:38:00.470
But we're still a
long way from there.

01:38:03.080 --> 01:38:06.937
Peter, could you just announce
Sari's next talk, please?

01:38:06.937 --> 01:38:07.436
Yeah.

01:38:07.436 --> 01:38:10.154
I got a technical
failure earlier.

01:38:10.154 --> 01:38:13.520
But I hope many of you know
that Professor Nusseibeh

01:38:13.520 --> 01:38:16.580
they will be giving a talk
this Thursday, as well.

01:38:16.580 --> 01:38:18.980
Which I suppose
the title relates

01:38:18.980 --> 01:38:20.870
in some ways to what
you were describing,

01:38:20.870 --> 01:38:23.560
the hopeful image of
a possible future.

01:38:23.560 --> 01:38:26.450
But this will address a more
academic and philosophical

01:38:26.450 --> 01:38:28.760
theme, Are Possible Facts Real?

01:38:28.760 --> 01:38:31.160
An Abyssinian Vignette.

01:38:31.160 --> 01:38:36.230
And this will be this Thursday
from 5 to 7 PM in the Tsai

01:38:36.230 --> 01:38:39.010
Auditorium, which is CGIS South.

01:38:39.010 --> 01:38:41.360
So I hope you'll all
come to hear Professor--

01:38:41.360 --> 01:38:44.450
But it's not about politics.

01:38:44.450 --> 01:38:47.630
And it may be still very
boring for a lot of you.

01:38:50.690 --> 01:38:51.380
And--

01:38:51.380 --> 01:38:53.000
I-- want to thank Sari.

01:38:53.000 --> 01:38:58.640
Because in fact, what you've
made us aware of in this both

01:38:58.640 --> 01:39:03.680
despairing and at the same
time, committed conversation--

01:39:03.680 --> 01:39:06.600
isn't there a Palestinian word
called [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:39:06.600 --> 01:39:07.410
or something?

01:39:07.410 --> 01:39:07.520
Yeah.

01:39:07.520 --> 01:39:07.730
Yes.

01:39:07.730 --> 01:39:07.960
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:39:07.960 --> 01:39:08.820
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH]

01:39:08.820 --> 01:39:09.650
We're here.

01:39:09.650 --> 01:39:10.490
I'm going to stay.

01:39:10.490 --> 01:39:11.270
I'm resilient.

01:39:11.270 --> 01:39:12.500
[NON-ENGLISH SPEECH].

01:39:12.500 --> 01:39:16.100
With that sentiment,
I think many

01:39:16.100 --> 01:39:18.050
of us in other
parts of the world

01:39:18.050 --> 01:39:19.940
have to take on
that same attitude.

01:39:19.940 --> 01:39:29.090
We live in a very, very divided,
ferociously uncaring situation

01:39:29.090 --> 01:39:29.590
now.

01:39:29.590 --> 01:39:31.230
And you see it in India.

01:39:31.230 --> 01:39:33.110
You see it of course in Turkey.

01:39:33.110 --> 01:39:37.580
In this country, where there
is plenty in some areas,

01:39:37.580 --> 01:39:40.250
you see it at every level.

01:39:40.250 --> 01:39:43.520
And of course, the most
ludicrous identification

01:39:43.520 --> 01:39:48.800
of those who are out of work
with an economic fraudster who

01:39:48.800 --> 01:39:52.940
is supposed to be the savior
or the sign of the future

01:39:52.940 --> 01:39:54.300
just makes you baffled.

01:39:54.300 --> 01:39:56.960
So that the things we don't
understand about the Middle

01:39:56.960 --> 01:40:00.140
East and about that region--

01:40:00.140 --> 01:40:02.360
there are many things we
don't understand here.

01:40:02.360 --> 01:40:05.960
And I hope in our
mutual vulnerability

01:40:05.960 --> 01:40:08.300
we will find both
knowledge and strength.

01:40:08.300 --> 01:40:09.140
Thank you.

01:40:09.140 --> 01:40:09.740
Thank you.

